title: chittling
directions: Clean and pick some fat (not all) off chittling and wash and clean thoroughly.
Put in water and boil for several hours until tender and done.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drop onion and white potato in chittling while cooking.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, melt butter and add sugar and Karo syrup.
Heat for 3 minutes in microwave oven.
Add baking powder and whip.
Pour mixture over popcorn in bag.
Microwave 1 minute. Shake hard.
Microwave one more minute and shake hard again. Microwave 30 seconds. Shake. Pur on countertop and break apart. Eat or store.
Makes a lot!

title: party chicken
directions: Cover bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch) with dried beef.
Wrap 1 strip of bacon around each chicken breast and arrange on dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
Dish can be prepared and refrigerated a day ahead before baking.
Serve with rice.
Serves 8 people.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions (tops and all), mushrooms and dried beef in blender.
Add to cream cheese and Accent.
Mix good and shape into a ball.

title: holiday salad
directions: In bowl dissolve Jello in the boiling water. Add cream cheese and stir until well blended. Add drained pineapple, celery and pecans. Place in refrigerator and chill for 30-45 minutes or until slightly thickened. Fold whipped topping into gelatin mixture. Pour into a 2-qt rectangular dish. Cover and chill for 4 to 24 hours. Garnish with cherries. Makes 8 servings.

title: potato chip cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla, flour and chips.
Mix well after each addition.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Let sugar and water come to a hard, rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Beat a while and add nuts; stir well.
Spoon on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into baking dish, enough to have dish full.
Mix lemon juice and water and sprinkle over apples.
Mix cinnamon, 1 tablespoon of flour and 1/2 cup sugar and sprinkle over apples.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 10-inch dish.
Stir in the pretzels and press evenly over the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add the whipped topping and spread mixture evenly over the pretzels.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add the strawberries. When it starts to jell, pour it on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: oat cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in a large saucepan and cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring often.
Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper and let cool.

title: broccoli and grape salad
directions: Cook bacon; let cool, then crumble.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Chop up red onion.
Mix together.
Pour dressing over just before serving.

title: apple spiced chicken salad
directions: Place butter, chicken breasts and diced celery in the seasoning sauce and cover.
Microwave for 14 minutes.
Turn and microwave 6 minutes.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Knead for 10 minutes; let rest 10 minutes.
Melt cube of butter on cookie sheet.
Roll dough on floured board; cut into strips.
Roll in butter and line on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Raise 10 minutes.

title: beef casserole all-in-one-dinner(serves 4)
directions: Mix ground beef with onion soup mix; place in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Put uncooked frozen vegetables over the meat.
Mix sour cream, cheese, butter, soup and curry together; mix that with the hash brown potatoes.
Place over vegetables. Bake, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover for the last 1/2 hour.
Delicious served with Scandinavian Tomato Salad.

title: sauerkraut and ribs
directions: Drain kraut; pour into baking dish.
Remove excess fat from meat; arrange on top of kraut.
Put in oven; bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: cuban ham
directions: Marinate 12 hours.
Mix juice and spices.
Make many slits in the top of the ham.
Pour mixture over it.
Cover ham with sliced onions and marinate 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, turning once and spooning the mixture over the top.
Slice thinly.

title: honey raisin drops
directions: Cream together honey, sugar, margarine, and egg.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° degrees for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except soup and shape into 20 balls.
Mixture will be soft.
Roll balls in flour and brown in 3 tablespoons
shortening.
Pour
off drippings and add can of soup with 1 can of water.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat egg well, add sugar and flour.
Beat again adding milk and vanilla.
Continue to beat 1 full minute at medium speed. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325 degrees until set.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Bring tomato soup to boil.
Add cream cheese, using wire whisk to blend.
Add gelatin, dissolved in 1/4 cup of water to soup and cream cheese mixture; cool.
Add remaining ingredients to cooled soup mixture.
Pour into oiled mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: empanadas(servings:  4)
directions: You will also need a 2-quart charlotte mold or bowl.

title: florentine potatoes
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until soft.
Add potatoes; saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook over high heat until slightly thickened.
Add spinach; heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ramen noodle cole slaw salad
directions: Combine cole slaw, almonds, sunflower seeds, oil, sugar and vinegar. Crush Ramen noodles with seasoning package. Add Ramen noodles right before serving.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer as follows:
rice, soup and water; mix.
Place chicken in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight jar.
Use 1 - 1 1/2 tsp. per cup of hot water.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all and eat!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables and seasoning in ungreased baking dish.
Stir baking mix and milk until blended. Pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter well.
Add bourbon and soda.
Sift flour with salt and spices; add to batter.
Sprinkle some of the flour over nuts and fruits.
Carefully combine all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for about 20 minutes or until desired brown is obtained.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Toss together cooked macaroni and vegetables.
Mix milk, mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetables.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain well.
Combine undiluted soup and cheese in heavy Dutch oven or crock-pot.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts.
Add sausage, picante sauce and milk.
Mix well.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and add to the cream mixture.
Mix in sliced apples (and nuts if you want).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in a large baking dish (greased or buttered). Place cut up chicken on rice.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put soup, water and onion in a bowl.
Mix well before pouring over chicken and rice.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°, then at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed to a boil.
Cool, then pour over the pickles and onions.
Stir well and put into container with lid on it at all times and keep it in the refrigerator until all are used.

title: granny's chicken noodle soup
directions: Will also need 1 small pot, 1 can opener, 1 bowl and 1 spoon.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt well.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil on high heat.
Turn on medium and cook about 20 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla after removing from heat.

title: debra's one stack dinner
directions: Place bacon in bottom of pan first.
Layer hamburger, season, sliced potatoes, season, then add green beans and season.
Heat on high until bacon sizzles, then turn heat down to simmer and cook for 1 hour.
Cover.
Add shredded cheese last. Let melt.

title: quick supper
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, pepper in a small amount of oil until potatoes are almost done.
Cut the Polish Kielbasa in 1/2 inch slices and add to potatoes.
Cook until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes on 350°.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown onion and beef; drain off fat.
Add other 7 ingredients and let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Leave room for cornbread.

title: crab stuffed chicken breast
directions: Beat egg lightly; add stuffing mix, 1/2 cup soup, crab meat, lemon juice, Worcestershire, mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt and mix well.
Sprinkle inside of chicken with 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Spoon 1/8 stuffing down center of each breast; roll and tie with strong cord.
Place on grill on low for approximately 45 minutes, turning often.
In pot, combine rest of soup with oil, milk, sauce, onion juice and dash of pepper.
Cook until soft boil.
Serve over grilled chicken.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large slow cooker, combine the first nine ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 7 to 8 hours or until the vegetables are tender.
Add milk and parsley; mix well.
Cover and cook 30 to 60 minutes longer or until heated through.
Garnish with chives if desired.

title: buttermilk sherbet
directions: Let freeze to mush.
Beat mixture with 2 egg whites and freeze.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon cheese on tortilla.
Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Add eggs, scramble.
Brown sausage, drain.
Mix with egg. Put on tortillas.
Fold and wrap in foil.
Cook at 300° for 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry salad dressing until well blended. Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in foil and chill. Will last for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: glazed raisin loaf
directions: Combine raisins, butter, sugar and salt in mixing bowl; add scalded milk.
Stir well, then cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add yeast, eggs and 1 cup flour to cooled raisin mixture and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour gradually, beating well to make a medium soft dough.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes, then knead on lightly floured surface until smooth, adding more flour as needed to prevent sticking. Place dough in greased bowl; grease surface of dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into a loaf and place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 30 minutes or until done.
When loaf is sufficiently brown, cover lightly with foil to finish baking.
Cool and glaze top with thin powdered sugar icing.

title: italian pork and chicken stew
directions: In large stock pot, combine shredded meats, tomatoes, tomato sauce, onions, bell pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Reduce to medium heat.
Sprinkle flour over top of vegetables. Gradually stir in broth.
Then add Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over medium heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in corn.
Continue cooking for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pinch cake
directions: Mix and melt oleo, sugar and cinnamon together.
Add raisins and pecans to mixture.
Grease Bundt pan lightly.
Place 2 cans cut biscuits in pan.
Pour a little mixture over and add the other 2 cans biscuits and the rest of the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: john's favorite chicken
directions: Fry chicken in shortening until brown.
Place in a 3 quart baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes. Pour over chicken and bake in 350° loven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: christmas snack crunch
directions: Combine butter, sugar and preserves in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until well blended and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients mixing until dry ingredients are coated.
Spread mixture evenly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Spread mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into bite sized pieces.
Store in tightly covered container in cool dry place. Yields 6 cups.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: grandma smith's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Put into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crumb Crust: Reserve 2 tablespoons of crumbs. Mix remaining crumbs and butter; press evenly on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan. Chill in refrigerator while preparing filling.

title: peaches and cream squares
directions: Mix cake mix, graham crackers, margarine, cinnamon and nuts together until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping. Add the egg to rest of mixture. Beat well.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan. Arrange drained peaches on top.
Mix cream cheese, frosting and 2 eggs. Pour over peaches. Sprinkle reserved topping on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until firm when shaken.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.

Prepare pastry. Stir together sugar, flour and orange rind. Turn half of the rhubarb into pie pan. Sprinkle half of the sugar mixture on this. Repeat with remaining rhubarb and sugar. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust. Put slits in top crust. Sprinkle with sugar. Cover edge of crust with aluminum foil. Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients except pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Lay pecans on top to cover surface. Bake at 350° for 50 min. If the edges begin to brown too early, cover with strips of aluminum foil.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: cabbage patch stew and dumplings
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, cabbage and celery. Cook until vegetables are light brown. Stir in tomatoes, beans, water, salt, pepper and chili powder. Heat mixture to boiling and reduce heat. Stir in Bisquick and milk. Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stew. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and egg.
Add flour.
Mix.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into cloverleaf or sandwich rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Pour over broccoli and cauliflower. Add cheddar cheese, onion, and bacon. Mix well. Refrigerate over night. Stir before serving. Makes a large bowl.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: In a 4-quart pot, saute onion, garlic, celery, parsley and bell pepper in cooking oil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Wash rice, then add to sauce.
Add shrimp.
Cover pot with tight fitting lid and cook on low fire until liquid is absorbed.
Stir once or twice while cooking.

title: ronco macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Todd with remaining ingredients.
Serve on salad greens.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Cut onion, peppers and eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and peppers. Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add eggplant, garlic, tomatoes, basil, paste, vinegar and salt to Dutch oven.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in red pepper seasoning and olives. Cook 10 more minutes.

title: spiders
directions: Heat morsels in microwave or on low heat.
Mix noodles and nuts into mixture.
Stir.
Drop onto wax paper with spoon.
Let dry.

title: fried okra
directions: Use tender, young pods.
Slice about 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch thick.
Use 2 parts cornmeal and 1 part flour to bread okra.
Put in bag; add sliced okra and shake until coated.
Fry in bacon grease until golden brown, turning often so it will not burn.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: layered salad
directions: In a 4-quart dish, shred lettuce.
Top with onion, celery, chestnuts and drained peas.
Spread mayonnaise over.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese, salt and garlic.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours. Before serving, sprinkle with eggs and bacon.

title: casa fiesta seven layer dip
directions: Mix sour cream with taco seasoning.
In shallow 12-inch bowl or	plate,	layer ingredients in the order listed.	Serve with chips.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut together; put in a greased cake pan. Mix cake mix and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together and spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cake is supposed to be gooey and could possibly fall apart.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Mix margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Put in jars and refrigerate.

title: beef barbecues
directions: Cut meat from bones into large pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and cook altogether, simmering for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or until meat shreds.
Makes about 24 barbecues.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with carrots, celery and cucumber slices.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cake mix, oil and egg on medium speed until crumbly. Add nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Fry green pepper gently in butter and oil for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and fry for 5 minutes more.
Transfer green pepper and mushrooms to a plate.
Stir flour into remaining butter and oil and cook for 2 minutes.
Gradually blend in milk and chicken stock or water.
Cook until sauce comes to a boil and thickens.
Lower heat to medium and add green pepper, mushrooms and chicken.
Cover the pan and cook thoroughly for ten minutes.
Beat cream with the egg yolks and wine or lemon juice.
Add to chicken mixture and cook 2 to 3 minutes more, but do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Add flour to yeast and
2 cups warm water to make extra thick batter.
Set in
warm
place
to
rise
overnight.
In morning add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
If batter is too thick, thin with water to desired thickness for baking.

title: lasagna(makes 3 casseroles, 6 servings each)
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
In large skillet, crumble beef and cook until slightly browned.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Drain off fat; add oregano, salt, garlic, parsley, water, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend eggs and cottage cheese.

title: chex school fuel
directions: Cover cookie sheet with waxed paper. Microwave brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup in large microwavable bowl covered on high 1 to 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minutes. Until margarine is melted. Stir in baking soda until dissolved. Stir in cereal. Microwave on high 3 minutes, stirring every minute. Spread on cookie sheet. Cool 10 minutes; break into bite-size pieces. Microwave chocolate chips in small bowl on high 1 minute 30 seconds or until chocolate is smooth. Drizzle chocolate over snack. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is set. Store in airtight container. 8 cups snack.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add chopped chilies, soups and sauce.
Cook until well mixed.
Place layers of tortillas on bottom of casserole dish.
Alternate layer of meat sauce.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cut okra into slices or leave whole if small.
Fry bacon pieces in a skillet, along with the onion.
Add okra and fry until it gets gooey.
Add the tomatoes, undrained, and vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper and continue cooking until okra is tender.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine pretzels, brown sugar and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Mix jello with boiling water and stir to dissolve; add cold water.
Add frozen strawberries, let mixture set part way.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: mexi dip
directions: Mix. Chill. Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 6 cups.

title: cold bean salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables, chop celery and onions finely. Mix sugar, vinegar and oil in small pan and bring to boil.
Mix all vegetables together.
Add liquid mixture and refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season and brown pork chops.
Place potatoes in alternate layers with sauce made of remaining ingredients.
Place pork chops on top and bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Remove cover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in pieces.
Flour and brown on both sides; remove from pan.
Roll onion in flour; brown in oil.
Layer meat and onion (covered with water) in covered casserole.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours.
Served with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: In a 9-inch square pan, mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa. Stir in milk, melted oleo and vanilla.
Spread batter in pan.
Then mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Will appear not to be done. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add eggs and pecans, chips, butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle onion rings on top. Bake 10 more minutes.

title: crab-cheese chowder(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan; add onion and celery.
Cook slowly until golden.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper; simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix
sugar,
milk
and oleo.
Add coconut and nuts; let set in
refrigerator until cooled good.
Roll in balls.
Melt chocolate
and
paraffin in top of double boiler and dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Store in tin container.

title: hurry shrimp curry
directions: In
top
of double boiler, saute onion and curry powder in butter
until
onion
is
soft.
Add other ingredients and simmer until heated through.
Serve over rice with condiments.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, gelatin, salt and spices. Combine egg yolks and milk; stir into brown sugar mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in pumpkin. Chill until mixture mounds slightly when spooned.

title: pina colada popcorn
directions: *To toast coconut, spread in a thin layer shallow baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 6 to 7 minutes or until light brown, stirring often.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Combine soup and broth.
Add chicken.
Heat over medium heat until fully heated.
On 8 individual plates, layer all ingredients, beginning with rice.
Next, add chicken mixture and cheese.
Add tomatoes, celery, onion, green pepper, pineapple and chow mein noodles.
Add more sauce, if desired.
Top with almonds.
Serves 8.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix in bowl.
Pour into ice cream maker.
Add milk
until 2/3 full.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, then add margarine and peanut butter. Pour over cereal and mix until cereal is completely covered.
Mix in bag of powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: scandinavian cucumbers
directions: Select one fresh from the market, not too green, but tender and healthy.
Handle gently, for they bruise easily.
Sweeten with smiles.
Blend with patience, humor and a pinch of mischief. Do not beat.
Preserve over a steady fire of warmth and affection. Like fine wine, they mellow with age.
Do not pickle or put in hot water.
This makes them bitter.
Serve with sugar, spice and tender loving care.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Mix all the ingredients; blend until moistened.
Beat as cake mix package directs.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on wire rack.
Fill and frost as directed.

title: triple chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions in a 9X13 pan.
Cool completely.
Cut cake into 1-inch squares and set aside.

title: peter pans
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter in microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into buttered pan 9 x 13-inches.
Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cindy denney's pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugar until fluffy. Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake approximately 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of bread comes out clean.

title: main baked fish chowder
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add 2 cups heated milk before serving.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Mix and roll out like any pastry.
Divide into 8 equal portions and roll out each piece flatter (not too thin though) using first 5 ingredients.
Put dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan; add apples to each section, then sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar and dash of cinnamon on each portion.
Fold edges over to cover apples going from corner to corner with a peak in middle.
Bake for 10 minutes or until brown at 350°, then using following ingredients, pour syrup over apples and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cream with butter.
Add eggs; mix and add buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: beef kabobs provencal
directions: Trim outside fat from steak and cut into 1-inch cubes. Combine wine, onion, oil, lemon juice, garlic, basil, sugar, salt, thyme and pepper.
Place beef cubes and marinade in plastic bag or utility dish, turning to coat meat.
Tie bag securely or cover dish and marinate in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours (or overnight).

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Roll cookies into balls and roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture (cinnamon and 1/4 cup white sugar).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
(You can also bake in 3 mini loaf pans filled halfway.
Makes great gifts!)

title: chicken casserole with cornbread dressing mix
directions: Pick chicken off bone, tear into small pieces and place in casserole
dish.
Mix sour cream, soups and one cup broth. Pour over chicken.
Mix 1/2 cup broth with dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: old fashion sugar cream pie
directions: Mix everything, except egg yolks, with spoon or hands.
Pat into a ball and spread out on a 9-inch pie plate.
Flute edges. Break egg yolk and coat the crust.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°. The egg coating seals the crust so the filling does not soak the crust.

title: layered salad
directions: Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours. Before serving, sprinkle with chopped hard-boiled egg and crisp bacon bits and decorate with sliced cherry tomatoes.
For a main dish, you may add cooked chicken or ham.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Blend butter, brown sugar and flour; spread over apples.
Mix 1 cup of sugar with the apples.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and mix them well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
You can make two pies from this recipe by adding more nuts.
I add approximately 1/2 cup more and make one deep dish pie.
Insert a knife in the center of the pie. If it comes out clean, it is done.

title: vanilla ice cream(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Separate the eggs and make a soft custard of the milk, egg yolks and sugar.
Beat the egg whites stiff and over them pour the hot custard and mix thoroughly.
Add the vanilla and salt, and when cold, the whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together; boil 1 minute.

title: meringue
directions: Place egg whites in a medium-sized mixing bowl. Beat on high speed with an electric mixer using the whisk attachment until frothy. Add cornstarch, cream of tartar Splenda Granular and vanilla. Beat on high speed until slightly stiff peaks form.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy, then add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Sift together 3 cups flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately to mixture with milk, then add vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
May be frosted, if desired.

title: glady's taco soup
directions: Brown first five ingredients together.
Then add remaining ingredients. Stir and simmer. Serve with shredded cheese and chips.

title: cheesy vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place pita breads on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread 2 tablespoons pizza sauce on each pita bread. Divide vegetables among pita breads.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 cup of cheese.
Bake 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat in saucepan and simmer 1 hour (heated until it starts thickening) then add meat.
Simmer for 1/4 to 1/2 hour.

title: tempted by pork sausage
directions: Form sausage into 3/4-inch balls. Brown slowly on all sides. Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat. Brown onion lightly. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick, about 20 minutes. Pour sauce into dish. Stick each sausage ball with toothpick and stand up in sauce. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: marie's delite dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Freeze 6 to 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with a cookie.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bread loaf pan.
In large bowl, stir together oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Stir in flour.
Roll into balls and flatten or roll out with rolling pin and cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate with raisins, etc.
Bake on slightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Cover.
Refrigerate 8 to 24 hours.
Do not stir!

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix sugar, graham crackers and butter.
Spread in large pie pan on bottom and sides.

title: savory chicken supreme
directions: Blend cream cheese and 1 tablespoon butter.
Add next ingredients, except seasoned bread crumbs and remaining butter. Mix well.
Lay out rolls.
Place 1/2 cup of chicken mixture in center of each, bring corners to center and pinch together.
Brush tops with butter and crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion and saute.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, rosemary and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Mix cottage cheese with eggs.
Start layering in oblong pan.
Use 1/2 meat mixture first.
Add layer of noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat for second layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until cheese is bubbly and browning.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Form dough into small balls and place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove at once.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruits and mix all together.
Add sour cream and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: salmon patties with creamed peas
directions: Combine first three ingredients, make 4 patties and fry until crispy on both sides.
Make a medium white sauce.
Add cooked peas. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve salmon patties with creamed peas spooned over.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool, peel and shred.
Melt butter.
Mix with shredded cheese, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and mix.

title: no syrup pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients above and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut beef across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Cover and refrigerate half of the beef and use within 2 days.
Cook and stir remaining beef in oil in 8-inch skillet over medium heat until brown.
Stir in water, soy sauce, sugar and instant bouillon. Arrange beef in one half of skillet.
Arrange onions and carrot in separate sections of skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Arrange celery, mushrooms and spinach in separate sections of skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until spinach is cooked, about 5 minutes. Serve with steamed rice.

title: pulled cream candy
directions: Mix sugar, hot water and soda in a large, heavy kettle.
Start boiling on high, then reduce to medium heat and let boil until it starts turning a cream color (248°).
Do not stir.
Pour on buttered marble slab.
Butter hands and start working until cool enough to hold in hands.
Start pulling and pull until it holds its shape (will be almost white in color).
Cut with scissors into pillows and cool on marble slab.
Can be eaten then or stored in airtight container.

title: cherry waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, prepare gelatin with 2 cups of boiling water and 1 cup of cold water.
Add lemon juice and then chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, nuts and celery.
Pour into lightly oiled 6-cup mold or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with apple slices. Makes approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Combine ingredients in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring often. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: coconut cream frosting(rave reviews coconut cake)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet. Add coconut; stir constantly over low heat until golden brown. Spread coconut on paper towel to cool. Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese. Add milk and beat in sugar gradually. Blend in vanilla. Stir in 1 3/4 cups coconut. Spread on top of cake layers. Stack and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: three pie shells
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add vinegar and water.
Mix well.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Divide into thirds.
Roll and fit into 3 pie plates.
Bake.
Can be frozen also and baked later.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pineapple in 9 x 12-inch ungreased cake pan.
Dump cherry pie filling evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts over cherry pie filling.
Put squares of margarine over cake mix.
Bake at 350°
for about 50 minutes.

title: banana bran muffins(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine mashed bananas and bran cereal in mixing bowl and mix well. Allow to stand for 5 minutes to soften the cereal. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt in another bowl and mix well. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine oleo and sugar; blend until smooth. Add egg and egg whites and mix thoroughly. Add banana mixture and mix well. Add flour and stir until you can't see dry flour.
Do not overmix.
Pour 1/3 cup batter into each of 12 muffin tins that have been sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating and bake about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water, then cool.
Mix cake mix with the eggs, oil and lemon flavoring.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Add Jell-O and mix again.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust (pierce crust with fork in several places on bottom to let any air bubbles out or crust may rise to top).
Sprinkle nutmeg and/or cinnamon on top. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; 325° until firm.

title: sesame fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut fish into 4 portions.
Place fish on a broiler pan lined with foil.
Brush olive oil over fish.
Combine lemon juice, basil, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over fish. Sprinkle sesame seed evenly over fish.
Broil until fish flakes easily when tested with fork or for about 12 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut icing
directions: Boil sugar, milk and coconut to the right consistency.
Cool in refrigerator until ready to spread on layers.
If too stiff, add small amount of milk.

title: corn salad(by sally sandruck)
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook until brown in 3 tablespoons butter, the beef and onion. Add and cook 10 minutes the beans and tomatoes.
Make a paste of chili powder, flour, water and salt.
Blend in and cook on low heat, stirring frequently for 45 minutes.

title: irish soda bread(great with irish corned beef and cabbage)
directions: Sieve dry ingredients into large bowl.
Scoop up handfuls and allow to drop back into bowl to aerate the mixture.
Add enough buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Work quickly now.
Knead dough lightly (too much handling will toughen it; too little and it won't rise properly).

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat well.
Cook in 2 or 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Saute chicken in hot butter in a large skillet for 5 minutes, turning once.
Add onion and garlic. Saute, covered, 5 minutes. Push chicken to one side of skillet.
Add spinach. Sprinkle with salt and basil.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly
ham,
pork,
eggs, cracker crumbs, milk and pepper.
Form into a loaf and bake in ungreased pan.
Stir together mustard,
brown
sugar, water and vinegar.
Pour over loaf and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste while baking.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and serve with sliced apples.
Strawberries are good as well.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli for about 5 minutes in a tiny bit of water and drain.
Mix in the blender the margarine, onion, eggs, cottage cheese, salt and muffin mix.
Fold the broccoli into the mixture. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in small balls.
Place in 8-inch square dish and cover with tomato soup and water.
Bake in moderate oven for 2 hours.

title: rainbow mints
directions: In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, beat together cream cheese and peppermint extract.
Add powdered sugar gradually and beat until smooth, kneading the last of the powdered sugar in with hands.
Form mixture into balls the size of a cherry and roll in rainbow sugar, if desired.
Place on waxed paper and flatten with a fork.
Let stand overnight.
Makes 3 dozen (1 inch) mints. Great for Easter.

title: old-fashioned potato bread
directions: Combine water and potato; bring to boiling.
Cook, covered, 12 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain!
Mash in water.
Add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Return mixture to pan. Add buttermilk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Heat or cool as necessary to 120° to 130°.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook chicken pieces slowly in hot oil until browned, turning once. Remove chicken, reserving oil in skillet. In same pan, cook celery, onions, green pepper and garlic until tender. Add

tomatoes, parsley, green onion, salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce and bay leaves. Cook, covered, 6 to 7 minutes. Add water, rice, wine and chicken pieces. Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cook, covered, over low heat about 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.

title: crab soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add celery, carrots, leek, green pepper, onion and 1 cup of broth.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
In separate pan, heat remaining broth with saffron to boiling point. Strain saffron and chicken broth mixture into first mixture.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add crabmeat and rice.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Remove from bone and combine with other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour at 375°.
Sprinkle top with butter and cracker crumbs before baking.

title: rattlesnake cake
directions: Mix it all at medium speed in electric mixer but do not beat too much.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Pour cake into pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients and bring to a boil over high heat.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes; remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Now add the oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir a minute, then drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Will harden as it cools.

title: e-z corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Place in a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old boy waffles
directions: Mix eggs, milk and oil in dry ingredients, then cook in waffler until brown.
Yield:
16 to 18 waffles.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cream cheese and pineapple. Mix with electric mixer.
Pour into square dish.
Refrigerate. When firm, spread with 1 container Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie
dough
into a pizza pan sprayed with Pam. Bake until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix powdered sugar and cream
cheese
together.
Pour
mixture over crust.
Next, add kiwi slices and pineapple spears to top of the pizza.

title: white cheese balls
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Process garlic with cheese in food processor.
Add enough mayonnaise to bind together.
Shape into 2 balls.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add strawberries, nuts, bananas and pineapple.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in casserole; let congeal. Spread with softened cream cheese.
Add remainder of Jell-O mix and let set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli until done in salted water.
Mix milk and soup and
pour
drained	broccoli
in
baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over
top.	Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out of oven; add onion rings and return to oven for 5 more minutes.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add orange juice and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: clifton's pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix first 6 ingredients together.

Gradually add cooking oil and mix thoroughly. Mix in pumpkin. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Blend well but do not overmix. Bake in three 9-inch pans for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Frost when completely cooled.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Mix with Miracle Whip.
Apple mixture to cracker.
Top with sliced cherry tomato.
Sprinkle cheese over cracker.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt chips. Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease 2 large cookie sheets. Cream the butter and sugar at medium speed until fluffy. Beat in egg, vanilla and melted chocolate. Add flour, baking soda and salt just until combined. Stir in nuts and oats. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheets.
Or roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Don't overcook for chewy cookies. Recipe may be doubled.

title: five grain quick bread(low calorie)
directions: Blend all ingredients in medium mixing bowl and put in 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set five minutes before turning out.

title: corn muffins
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Combine beaten egg, milk and shortening. Pour into dry ingredients.
Stir, do not beat, until moistened. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: k. c.'s baklava
directions: Mix walnuts, sugar and spices.
Grease 11 x 16-inch pan with melted butter.
Place 8 phyllo in pan, brushing each with melted butter; sprinkle 1/3 nut mixture, then 3 buttered phyllo, 1/3 nut mixture, 3 buttered phyllo, 1/3 nut mixture, then the remaining phyllo.
Brush each one and layer on top until all the dough has been used.
Cut pastry into small diamond shapes.
Bake at 250° until golden brown (about 1 1/2 hours).
Remove from oven and cool.
Pour warm syrup over pastry.
Do not cover until it's completely cooled.

title: thrifty casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook, stirring, with a fork to break up meat, until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole, bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
In a large shallow baking dish, shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Microwave first three ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add butter and 1 1/2 c. cheddar.
Stir until melted.
Then mix the beaten eggs into the grits mixture.
Pour this into a buttered 8 by 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and paprika over grits mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into 15 x 10-inch pan to form a crust. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Combine cheese, mayonnaise and spices. Top with desired vegetables, grated carrots, chopped tomato, onion, broccoli, etc., black olives or grated cheese. Sprinkle with seasoning salt. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add all other ingredients.
Measure oatmeal before blending. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet, leaving 1-inch gap between cookies.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Season chicken with pepper and garlic salt.
Grill over high heat for 10 to 12 minutes until done.
Chop into bite size pieces. Add spaghetti to boiling water and boil 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and continue to boil 5 minutes more. Drain. Add chicken to spaghetti and vegetables.
Mix well. Coat with dressing.
Serve warm or chilled.
Contains approximately 137 calories per cup.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Stir in soup, sour cream and paprika.
Add water to thin.
Heat through and serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: confetti omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon; crumble bacon. Saute onion in bacon fat until tender.
Combine onion, bacon, eggs, milk, pimiento, parsley and salt.
Toss Cheddar and Swiss cheese in flour; add to egg mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add boiling water to raisins and cook for 5 minutes.
Cool. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add cooled raisins and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour. Add salt, soda, baking powder, spices and chopped nuts; blend. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans to form a ball and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bob's cornbread
directions: Mix together cornbread mix, flour, egg, sugar and margarine or oil. Add buttermilk until it has consistency of a cake. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. If any way possible, bake in an iron skillet.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread cubes and cheese.
Top with cheese and bread cubes.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes; cook in salted water.
Add finely chopped onion, celery and eggs.
Add to cooked potatoes.
Stir in Marzetti slaw dressing.
Add additional dressing if needed to make it creamy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill before serving.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and add graham cracker crumbs.
Pat lightly to make crust.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, coconut, butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour milk over top. Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Pour sweet milk over okra.
Mix other ingredients together. Roll okra in meal mixture.
Cook individually in hot oil.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, 1/4 cup melted oleo, salt, onion, cream of chicken soup, yogurt and grated cheese in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Combine cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Spread on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar until dissolved.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, alternating with eggs, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, chopped apples, nuts and coconut. Batter will be thick.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: make-ahead grilled salad
directions: Prepare a hot fire.
Brush yellow squash, zucchini and onion with oil.
Grill 6 inches from coals, turning occasionally until vegetables are slightly browned and softened (5 to 7 minutes). Remove from heat and let cool.
Slice vegetables.
In a large bowl, combine grilled vegetables, salad dressing, salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Drain vegetables and arrange on serving platter.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain; cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
You can use taco seasoning in meat mixture if you want.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon-colored.
Add small amount of flour to yolks; gradually add sugar and remaining flour.
Add melted oleo, stirring constantly.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour until firm.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown hamburger meat and ground sausage and then drain the grease off.
In a large pot, combine the hamburger and sausage with Velveeta cheese.
Add the cayenne pepper and seasonings. Preheat oven to 350°.
Take the loaf of pumpernickel bread and cut each slice in half.
Take a spoonful of the mixture and put onto each half of the bread.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam and just slightly toast the bread with mix.
This usually takes about 15 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Arrange cut peaches in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400 degrees.
Mix together egg, sugar and cornstarch and add to peaches.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: orange-pecan buttermilk bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pans. Peel orange and place peel and sugar in food processor. Process until finely chopped.
Place flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; add orange and sugar mixture.
In smaller bowl, place egg, orange juice, buttermilk and vegetable oil; mix well and pour into flour mixture.
Mix with a few quick strokes.
Do not overmix.
Fold in pecans. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven 50 minutes or until done.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, Crisco, butter and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add milk and boil slowly 3 minutes, stirring.
Cool.
Add 10x sugar and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients at once, stirring just until moistened.
Don't overmix.
Crush 1/2 cup of berries.
Add to batter.
Fold in remaining berries and spoon into muffin pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes or until done at 375°.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack.
Makes 12.
Each contains 250 calories.

title: brittanie's favorite taco dip
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Heat to boiling.
Let simmer 15 or 20 minutes.

title: zucchini de la torte
directions: In large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and oil; salt and pepper.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 small casseroles 45 minutes or until done.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients, milk last.
Mix well.
Will be very thin.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil, sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let jell; add cut up strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and chill again (at least 4 hours) before serving.

title: custard pie
directions: Chill pie shell while making filling.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: buster bars
directions: Mix crushed Oreo cookies and mix with 1/2 cup melted oleo. Pat all but 1/3 cup in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 1 hour.
Spread softened ice cream on crust.

title: coconut torte
directions: Mix together and pat in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: shrimp pasta sauce
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine olive oil, mushrooms, zucchini, onion, parsley, garlic, basil and thyme.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 3 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, stirring to break apart tomatoes.
Cover with wax paper.
Reduce power to 70% (Medium-high).
Microwave for 10 to 15 minutes until flavors are blended, stirring once.
Stir in shrimp.
Re-cover.
Microwave at 70% for 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp is opaque, stirring once. Let stand covered for 3 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked pasta. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain. Cook noodles as directed and drain. Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add to this the remaining ingredients.
Mix with electric mixer until blended (don't overmix).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: *You may use all margarine, if you wish.

title: rib-eye potato butter
directions: Blend butter and
bacon fat in a mixing bowl until soft and gently blend in the remaining ingredients.

title: festive seven-layer gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into sprayed 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Bring milk to boil in a saucepan.
Add sugar and mix until dissolved. Add unflavored gelatin which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add sour cream and vanilla and beat until blended.
Cool. When lime Jell-O is set, pour 1 1/2 cups of white mixture over. When white layer is sticky, add red Jell-O, prepared in sme manner as the lime.
When set, add another 1 1/2 cups of the white mixture.
Follow with lemon layer.
Top with final white layer.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix all vegetables together and pour vinegar mixture over them.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Turn crock-pot on high.
Place roast in pot, along with soup mix.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Mix mushroom soup with can of water; pour over vegetables.
Cook 3 to 4 more hours, or until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and season to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm on crackers.

title: spicy prune ring cake
directions: Pour boiling water on prunes in large mixing bowl.
Let stand 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour Bundt pan. Beat prunes and remaining ingredients for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake until cake tests done, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool completely. Frost with Orange Glaze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
When done combine all ingredients in bowl, place in baking dish.
Bake on 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "perfect apple pie"
directions: If apples lack tartness, sprinkle with about 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all together in freezer; fill freezer can with milk.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix and let chill until very firm.
Make topping after mixture has chilled.

title: egg brunch casserole
directions: Blend eggs and milk.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
If casserole looks dry before baking, add a little more milk and egg.

title: praline butter chocolate torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Split cake to make 4 layers.
Beat brown sugar and whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Fill each layer with 3/4 cup of the whipped cream mixture.
Garnish with whole pecans, if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: microwave buttermilk candy
directions: In a large microwave-oven-safe bowl, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk, and butter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Punch holes in wrap.
Cook in microwave oven for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir and turn dish.

Continue cooking for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Return to oven for every 2 minutes, or until soft ball forms in cold water, or it tests 235° to 236° on candy thermometer (do not put thermometer in microwave unless it's microwave-safe).
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Stir in pecans, and spread in buttered 12x7-inch dish.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a 1-quart casserole or a 2-cup measure.
Stir in water and cook 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Blend in butter.
Cook 30 seconds, stirring halfway through.
Remove from oven and stir in vanilla.

title: tuna ring
directions: Soften gelatin in water in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Set aside.

title: pioneer sugar cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth. Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown
hamburger
and drain.
Stir in cheese and relish and let
simmer for a while.
Serves approximately 25 people. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Mix cheese, pineapple, onion and pepper.
Roll into a ball or log.
Sprinkle parsley onto waxed paper.
Roll cheese ball in parsley until coated.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: poor man's chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef and hamburg together.
Drain off excess fat. Dissolve bouillon in 1 cup of water.
Add to meat.
Chop celery, onions, pepper and mushrooms.
Add to meat and cook over medium heat until all is cooked and tender.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix last 6 ingredients and add apple mix; blend well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: georgia peach bread recipe
directions: Place peaches and 6 tablespoons sugar in blender and process until pureed (mixture should yield about 2 1/4 cups).
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream 1 1/2 cup sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add peach puree and dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn on rack and cool completely.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add taco seasoning pack.
Cook as directed.
Add refried beans, chilies, 2 cups of cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until it bubbles.
Remove from oven; dab sour cream all over top.
Layer with remaining cheese, chopped green onions and olives.
Serve with corn chips.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix rice, mushroom soup, celery soup and water.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 envelope of onion soup over rice mixture.
Place skinned chicken on soup and rice. Sprinkle remaining envelope of onion soup over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Don't peek!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Place half macaroni in ungreased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with half the onion, salt, pepper and cheese; repeat. Pour White Sauce over casserole and dot with butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: quick muffins
directions: Break egg into a bowl; whisk with a fork.
Add milk and oil to egg; blend with a mixer briefly.
Sift dry ingredients together, then stir into egg mixture just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Fill well-greased muffin cups 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients in 3 additions.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into tube pan or 15-inch oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8 inch slices.
Line foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate; carefully remove foil.
Invert to right side.

title: coconut cream dream cake
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream and about 1/2 of the coconut together; let chill.
Mix and bake cake according to box directions.
Cut cake into layers with a string when cool.
Separate 1 c. of sugar and sour cream mixture and spread remaining mixture between cake layers.
Mix cool whip with reserved mixture and put on sides and top of cake.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of coconut on top and sides of cake.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Place in 1-inch deep baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Combine soup, green pepper and onion with the beaten egg and pour over the macaroni.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Add oregano, basil and garlic powder to tomato sauce.
Pour over macaroni mixture and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: grandma's best cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and mix.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix baking soda and salt with flour; add to creamed mixture.
Add the coconut.
Add oatmeal and corn flakes.
If desired, add 1/2 cup raisins and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mixture will be thick.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly with back of wet spoon.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: cutter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll thin as cookie cutters; bake at 375° just until edges begin to turn brown.
Leave 2 inches between raw cookies.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in pretzel crumbs and press into dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Let cool completely. Beat cream cheese and sugar together until smooth.
Spread over crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and chill.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice, then stir in frozen strawberries.
Let begin to congeal, then pour over white layer.
Let all refrigerate until set.

title: daddy's cornbread
directions: Put 1
tablespoon
bacon grease in iron skillet and put in oven
to
heat.
Turn
oven on to 425°.
(Heating pan first keeps the
cornbread
from
sticking.)
Mix
all	ingredients together: flour, cornmeal, salt, baking powder, egg, milk and sugar.	Stir lightly and pour in greased pan in oven.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients (except the bacon) in the 2 1/2-quart deep casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Top with bacon.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix this together and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add milk as necessary to create a medium batter consistency.
Pour into a large thin casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes; until golden brown and center is done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, add all but flour.
Beat well.
Add flour and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° or until a toothpick or knife comes out clean.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Combine egg and milk.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients alternately with creamed mixture.
Roll on floured surface 1/4-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Put in an airtight container while still warm.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 (13 x 9-inch), 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: turtles
directions: Cook the Eagle Brand milk, brown sugar, Karo syrup, butter, salt and vanilla to a soft ball stage.
Take pecan halves and place in 3's on aluminum foil or wax paper to resemble a turtle. Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Pour caramel over the pecans by the spoonfuls and then cover with the melted chocolate.
Cool well.
Enjoy!

title: pasta fagouli
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add the can of beans, cooked and drained spinach and macaroni.
Add the can of chicken broth.
Simmer and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Put yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup water.
When yeast has dissolved, add to buttermilk and soda.

title: chocolate cream fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and chocolate syrup. Fold in Marshmallow Creme. Cover and refrigerate. Dip apple wedges, strawberries, banana chunks, etc.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add melted chocolate, beaten egg and mix.
Add cake flour, baking soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, then cold water.
Mix well.
Slightly grease and flour pan (9 x 13-inch) and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Use favorite chocolate icing.

title: chocolatetown cupcakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add alternately with syrup to creamed mixture.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups (2 1/2-inches diameter) half full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost as desired.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: onion special
directions: Core out 1/3-inch of peeled onion and put 1/2 bouillon cube in hole.
Use 1 whole cube for large onion.
Wrap each onion in foil and cook on hot grill or oven, 350° to 400° for 45 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Remove seeds and chop tomatoes.
Drain and rinse black eyed peas.
Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill for 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: apple berry spritzer
directions: Mix juice concentrate, sparkling water and cider. Slice orange thinly and add to mixture. Serve over ice.

title: ham glaze
directions: Combine syrup and marmalade.
Brush on ham during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Makes 1 cup of glaze, enough to glaze a 10 pound ham.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350° with cookies sheets ready.
With wooden spoon, mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Dough will be sticky.
With floured hands, roll a tablespoon of dough into balls.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookie looks dry with cracked tops.
Remove and press chocolate kiss in center of each.
Cook 1 to 2 more minutes and remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 48.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Follow directions according to cake mix box and bake as directed in 2 round cake pans.
Allow cakes to cool completely. Drain pineapple and save juice.
Using a fork or toothpick, punch holes in layers and dribble some of the juice over the cake.
Mix pineapple and Cool Whip together.
Spread small amount of mixture between layers.
Use the rest to ice entire cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: buried treasure
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box. Using a spoon, scoop out 4 balls of frozen cool whip. Place in each desert glass. Spoon pudding over whipped topping in glasses. Chill.

title: railroad pie
directions: Brown beef with onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Add can of tomato soup with can of water.
Add corn, bell pepper and chili powder.
Simmer and reduce heat.
In a separate bowl, mix corn meal, flour, sugar, egg, oil and milk.
Stir and spoon over railroad pie.
Bake at 400° until cornbread is brown.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat to boil, stirring frequently until thick.
Serve over hot biscuits with butter.

title: my favorite snack:  toast of cinnamon
directions: Take cinnamon and butter and mix with a spoon in a bowl. Take two pieces of bread and cut it up with a knife.
Put it in the microwave for a minute.
Take it out and Walla!

title: beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch; add vinegar and beet juice. Bring to boil; simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add beets; simmer a little longer.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Excellent vegetable dip or can also be used in the center of a dark round loaf of bread.

title: lettuce parmesan
directions: Tear or chop lettuce, cut celery diagonally.
Place lettuce, celery and onion rings in layers.
Combine sour cream and sugar; drizzle over the layers.
Combine mayonnaise and vinegar, drizzle over layers and sour cream.
Crumble cooked bacon over salad. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: walnut butter bars(easier than baking batches of cookies!!!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter or spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: In casserole dish, put rice and water.
Let set while chopping onion and celery.
Add onion and celery to rice.
Add mushroom soup and broccoli.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Bake for 1 hour in 425° oven, uncovered.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light.
Add eggs, well beaten. Then stir in bananas.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, buttermilk, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle meat lightly with garlic powder.
Put in heavy casserole or Dutch oven. Mix together remaining ingredients, except carrots, and pour over meat.
Mix well.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat soup, milk, water and enchilada sauce in pan.
Line baking dish with tortillas.
Cover with layer of meat, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy cheese soup
directions: Combine water, potatoes, carrots, onion, celery, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cream cheese.
Add milk.
Blend together butter and flour and melt in saucepan.
Cook until thickens.
Add to soup; cook and stir until mixture thickens.

title: squash dish
directions: Stir-fry the first 6 ingredients for about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
May be served hot or cold.

title: carolyn's dirty rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix everything else and bake in casserole, covered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: peach crisp
directions: Mix fruit with 1 tablespoon melted butter, salt, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Cream 3 tablespoons butter; mix in sugar and flour.
Add cereal and crumble together. Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 25 minutes or until crisp.
(Best served warm.
Use Cool Whip or ice cream topping, optional.)

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Cook sausage and chopped onion until brown. Drain off fat and set aside. Combine cornmeal and other dry ingredients. Beat eggs, buttermilk and oil together and pour over dry ingredients. Add sausage, onion, bell pepper, corn and peas. Then add in grated cheese. Make sure muffin tins are sprayed generously with Pam nonstick spray. Pour about 1/3 of muffin tin with mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: roasted red potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into quarters.
Place in medium size roasting pan.
Slice butter over potatoes.
Add spices to your taste.
Top with chopped garden onions and chives and baking bits. Bake in oven at 375 degrees for 35 minutes.
When finished top with shredded cheese and serve with sour cream.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: nanna puddin'
directions: Mix pudding in large bowl with milk, nutmeg, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Add cream until desired texture is obtained (usually 2/3 can will be used).

In large serving bowl layer wafers, one sliced banana; add pudding mix (1/3 mixture), wafers, one sliced banana, 1/3 pudding mixture, wafers, one sliced banana, remaining pudding. Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg.
Chill 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: make your own shake and bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use on whatever you would like to cook.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Bake in 3 pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: meat balls in mushroom gravy
directions: Mix together beef, egg, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Brown meat balls on all sides in a skillet.
Pour off fat.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in casserole dish and bake one hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix these ingredients well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan or jellyrole pan. Bake according to cooking directions on cake mix box. Prepare frosting by mixing 1 stick melted oleo, 1 box powdered sugar, 1 cup chopped nuts, 1 (8 oz.) package cream cheese and 2 teasspoons vanilla. Spread on cake.

title: berries and bits
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in beaten whipping cream.
Spoon in 2 cups pudding mix into a 3-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/2 the wafers, then 1/2 the strawberries, then 1/2 the bits.
Repeat layering.
Garnish with bits on top. Chill.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Sift alternately with the hot water.
Pour into a well-greased pan and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt. In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to the flour mixture, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or two smaller pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix Ranch dressing and cream of chicken soup together. Spread over 8 chicken breasts (boneless is best) and sprinkle bread crumbs over chicken, enough to cover well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: country cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in a large bowl. Cover with Marzetti slaw dressing. Mix well. Add coarse black pepper (the kind that sticks to your teeth) and refrigerate. When serving, finish with a hint of dill.

title: grandma pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately having added the baking powder to the last addition of flour.
Last add flavoring.
Use electric mixer.
