Pour into a round tube pan which has been greased thoroughly.
Flour lightly and place in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open door until time is up.
Do not turn on oven until cake is in it.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour one time and measure.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; sift again.
Combine sugar and oil in separate bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Add carrots; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Add vanilla.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and blend.
Grease tube pan.
Bake at 350° (preheated oven) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Secret is in the blending; blend well.)
Frost or use powdered sugar when cool.

title: company-hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add green chilies and sour cream, barely heating.
Add hominy, cumin seed and 1/2 grated cheese, heating until cheese melts.
Pour into baking dish and top with rest of the grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: white texas cake
directions: First bring water and margarine to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add last 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of pan.
Layer cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, salsa and Cheddar cheese on top of beans.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tuna pasta bake
directions: Place lasagna in 12 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with water and set aside.
Combine onion, oil and flour.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve flour.
Stir in vegetables and milk. Cook on High 4 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in lemon juice. Combine 1 cup Mozzarella, cottage cheese, Parmesan, egg and pepper.
Drain lasagna.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Cook egg, vinegar and sugar until thickened.
Pour warm egg mixture into creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill.

title: apricot bread("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Cut apricots into coarse pieces and pour 1 cup boiling water over them.
Set aside to cool, stirring once or twice.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, beating well again.
Stir apricot and water mixture and then fold into flour mixture until blended.
Break walnuts into pieces and add to batter.
Grease loaf pan and line with waxed paper.
Pour in batter and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef reuben melts
directions: In medium skillet, combine ground beef, onion, and garlic; cook over medium-high heat for 8-10 minutes or until beef is thoroughly cooked and onion is tender, stirring frequently. Drain.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion and
celery
in
butter for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in sausage,
gravy and peas.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour
into
a
9-inch
deep-dish
pie pan; dot with butter.
Combine
mashed
potatoes
and
parsley; spoon around edge of pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes until heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Combine oil, 1 cup sugar, egg, buttermilk, baking soda, flour and salt; beat well. Pour half of batter into a greased bread pan. Combine cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. Sprinkle half of cinnamon-sugar mixture over batter. Pour in rest of batter and sprinkle remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice for the crew(10 people)
directions: Boil chicken pieces in large pot with 2 gallons water, onions, celery and livers for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove chicken, let cool and debone (optional) or leave in pot; skim off grease. Mixing well stir in all soup, returning to a boil.
Slowly stir in rice.
Cover with a tight fitting lid.
Reduce heat.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat; let stand for 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cornbread.
Halve ingredients for 5 people.

title: chocolate cherry cheesecake cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line 24 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Slice well chilled cookie dough into 24 slices. Place slices in bottom of muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, flour, margarine, vanilla, cream cheese and eggs; beat 1 minute.
Top cookie slices with cream cheese mixture, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes; tops should be light golden brown.
Natural indentation will form at center. Cool completely to serve; top with pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup oleo to hot mixture and cool.
Add eggs, liquid sweetener, vanilla, soda, flour and nuts, if desired.
Chill 2 hours.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
about 4 dozen cookies.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and molasses.
Cook until spins thread.
Add butter; cook until forms hard ball.
Add soda; pour over popcorn, mixing thoroughly.
Wet and grease hands; form balls while still hot.
When balls are cooled, wrap in wax paper, twisting ends.
I fill two large bowls or Dutch ovens with popcorn.

title: texas beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and green pepper in oil until transparent (yellow).
Remove cooked vegetables from pan and set aside.
Cook ground beef, dipping out fat as it accumulates in pan.
Cook until the beef is well done and falls into small pieces.
Drain beef on paper towels.
Place drained beef in large bowl.
Stir in onions, green pepper and remaining ingredients. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish with lid.
Cover and bake 1 hour, removing cover for last 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In a pan, melt butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth. Cook until mixture thickens and boils; boil 1 minute. Brown pork chops in oil. Set oven at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place
biscuits in freezer for 15 minutes.
Remove from freezer
and
cut
into quarters.
Shake biscuits in sugar and cinnamon
mix.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Layer biscuits in pan,
putting
nuts
and raisins between layers.
Cook 1 stick margarine
and
1 cup brown sugar for 1 minute.
Pour over all and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring often, 5 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and let stand 30 minutes to cool.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Grind all vegetables; sprinkle with the pickling salt.
Let stand overnight; rinse and drain.
Combine the sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, vinegar and 2 cups water.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Fill hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.

title: creamed chicken delight
directions: In pan, cook carrot, celery and onion with thyme in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, water and chicken.
Heat and serve over toast.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pineapple dream cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in pineapple. Mix together and stir in flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix in nuts or more to taste.
Drop rounded teaspoonful on baking sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cutlets parmesan
directions: Using a sharp knife, remove and discard any excess fat and gristle from chicken breasts.
Cut away white tendon from fillet. Place one breast half, smooth side down, between two sheets of waxed paper.
Pound cutlet until it is about 1/8-inch thick. Discard waxed paper; repeat process with remaining breast halves. Dust pounded cutlets with flour on clean sheet of waxed paper; shake off any excess.
Mix together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic salt in shallow bowl.
Dip each cutlet first in egg mixture and then in crumb mixture.
Set cutlets aside on wire rack until ready to cook.
Heat oil in skillet over moderate high heat until almost smoking.
Place 2 cutlets in skillet and fry until crisp and golden brown.
Turn over with tongs and fry on other side about 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and fry remaining cutlets in same manner.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Roll balls in mixture; place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until set. Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
For soft cookies, undercook.

title: aunt elsie hulnick's veal loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Prepare 24 hours in advance and refrigerate.
Place in casserole with cooked potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute in butter the onion, celery, garlic, green onion and bell pepper. *Use a large-deep skillet.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9x5 inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, beat first 10 ingredients well. Pour into loaf pan smooth top. Combine last 3 ingredients until crumble. Sprinkle on top of batter. Bake 50 minutes.

title: hot slaw
directions: Shred cabbage rather fine.
Chop celery.
Put in a saucepan and sprinkle with salt.
Cover pan and place over a low heat; steam until very tender.
Beat the egg; add the sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper, onion salt and celery salt and pour over the steamed cabbage.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: black pepper pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Beat butter in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar to butter.
Beat 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour. Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Let stand, covered, overnight.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine pecans, cracker crumbs, raisins, cherries, and pineapple.
In a large saucepan, combine marshmallows, milk, and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Pour over pecan mixture and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in the coconut, washing your hands frequently.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: baked eggplant sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 1 tablespoon oil in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut eggplant into twelve 1/2-inch slices.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce onto 6 eggplant slices.
Top each with 1 slice of cheese and then top with other eggplant slices.
Beat eggs and milk.
Put bread crumbs and parsley in a bowl.
Dip each sandwich in egg batter, then coat with bread crumbs, even around edges.
Put sandwiches in pan.
Drizzle with remaining oil.
Cover with foil. Bake 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Turn sandwiches and bake 20 minutes more until brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on 2 pizza pans.
Bake as directed.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch style dressing mix a day ahead so flavors can blend (keep refrigerated).
Spread on baked crust.
Chop vegetables fine.
Spread vegetables on cream cheese.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: dairy queen blizzard
directions: Break the candy bar into tiny pieces with a knife handle before removing the bar from wrapper.
Combine all of the ingredients in the blender; blend for 30 seconds on medium speed. Stop the blender to stir the mixture with a spoon.
Repeat until well mixed.
Pour into a 16-ounce glass.
Makes 2 servings or 1 extra large serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Spoon into prepared pie crust. Crimp edges to seal. Slit top crust and brush with beaten egg, if desired. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Add flour, Crush and flavor; mix well.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, pepper, onion, celery and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over this.
Then sprinkle sugar.
Sprinkle cheese and then crumble bacon.
Cover with Saran Wrap for 24 hours.
Keeps well for several days.

title: "beefy" beef stew
directions: Cook bacon in 4-quart pot, stirring occasionally until cooked. Remove from pot.
Add beef and brown.
Add 2 cups of water, salt, thyme, marjoram and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in onions, carrots and potatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Mix 1/2 cup cold water and flour; gradually stir into stew.
Stir in browning sauce.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Sprinkle with parsley and bacon.

title: unleavened cottage cheese rolls
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours. Separate into three balls of dough.
On a well floured surface, roll out each ball separately as you would pie crust until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into triangles and roll them, starting at the wide end so they look like crescent rolls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornish hens in orange sauce
directions: Soak hens in salt water; dry.
Brush with melted butter and place, skin side down, in broiler pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat; simmer for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and brush hens with sauce.
Roast for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn, roasting 30 minutes longer, or until brown.
Baste often.
Makes 8 servings. Each serving contains 298 calories.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and blend until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
With a fork dipped in flour, flatten each round of dough by pressing a crisscross design on top of each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: japanese style chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge chicken pieces.
Heat oil in large skillet; add chicken and brown well on both sides. Turn chicken skin side up and add water.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Place chicken on a platter and keep warm. Add soy sauce and vegetables to skillet.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, separating vegetables with a fork; stir until sauce cubes are blended.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes. Serve over chicken with rice, if desired.
Makes 3 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve in a whole rye bread boat.
Put bread chunks around the boat for dipping. Have an extra loaf of rye bread to break up to put around boat for dipping in.

title: cheryl's quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare pie shell.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface until it is about 3-inches larger than quiche pan.
Fit dough into the quiche pan.
Trim edges; fold under and flute.
Do not prick the pastry shell.
Bake 7 minutes. Remove from oven and set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole(family reunion size)
directions: Heat potatoes and drain.
Mash up potatoes and add other ingredients.
Put in large pan.

title: grapefruit jelly
directions: Add sugar to juice and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add pectin and boil 1 minute.

title: zesty spinach salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in jar with tight fitting lid. Shake and mix well; refrigerate.
Just before serving, lightly toss the remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Shake dressing well, then pour over salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: greg's soup-er desserts cheese torte
directions: Crust:
Mix and line buttered pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over crumbs and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: rocks
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar; add eggs, then add raisins, nuts and dates (cut up).
Add soda dissolved in the hot water and the flour.
Drop cookies on cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at about 400° until brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda.
Combine oleo, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: divinity surprise drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Continue beating; gradually add sugar.
Fold in vanilla extract and chocolate chips.

title: red taters and sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add cheese.
Add diced Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Melt and blend.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put milk on stove and add 1/4 cup sugar.
Let get hot but not boiling.
Put the rest of sugar in bowl with cornstarch and add some milk to make paste.
(I use a little milk out of container for this.)
Add egg yolks and beat.
When milk gets hot, add this mixture to milk and stir until thick.
Add coconut.

title: best banana muffins or bread
directions: Beat together sugar, vanilla and butter.
Add banana and yogurt.
Add mixture of dry ingredients.
Blend in Grape-Nuts. Pour into muffin cups and bake 16 minutes at 375°.

title: italian beef
directions: Put roast, water, bouillon and paprika in roaster.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Take roast out of liquid, cool, then slice thin.
Heat liquid and add the remaining ingredients. Pour over meat slices and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: quick cockeyed cake
directions: Put sifted flour into bowl.
Add cocoa, soda, sugar and salt. Mix well.
Put into a greased square pan, about 9 x x 9 x 2-inch. Make 3 holes in dry mix.
Into one hole, pour oil, next one pour vinegar and last one the vanilla.
Pour cold water over all.
Beat with a spoon until nearly smooth and you can't see the flour. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mom's pickin' cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits in 1/4's.
Melt margarine, sugar and cinnamon to blend.
Add nuts (chopped).

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake 40 minutes in 300° oven then let stand 5 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 2 loaf pans with vegetable cooking spray.
In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat together the sugar, oil and eggs.
In a separate bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture to batter; mix just until blended.
Stir vanilla, apples and pecans into batter.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Yields 2 loaves, 16 servings each.
Each serving contains 189 calories (47% from fat).

title: tuna cheese bake
directions: Combine cheese, tuna, 1/4 cup bread crumbs and seasoning. Blend into beaten eggs.
Place in casserole dish (1-quart). Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs (buttered).
Set casserole in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots and mix.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Store in covered container for at least 10 hours prior to serving time.
Serves 25 to 30.
May also be used by a family. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, margarine and milk in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until creamy. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine dry ingredients and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: dorothy's buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and cornmeal.
Add eggs, oleo, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: zesty gouda spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers. Makes about 2 cups.

title: cranberry apple muffins(makes 12 regular muffins)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups or use foil cups to line muffin pan.

title: do little seven squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients in layers in given order.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Press slightly with spatula while still hot.
Let cool in pan; cut in desired squares.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Scatter raw ground beef over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Mix canned soups with milk and pour over meat.
Arrange Tater Tots on top, side by side. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: onion-potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, salt and pepper slowly in covered pan until tender.
Cover potatoes about 4 inches over with water as to have some potato juice left when done cooking.
Add 3 cups of milk and butter.
Add 1/3 cup instant potatoes to soup or more if a thicker soup is desired.

title: cream puffs(midget puffs)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to high boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat, about 1 minute, or until forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs all at one time until smooth.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: amy's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour. Spread evenly in a large rectangular greased pan.
Brush lightly with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into small squares.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat raisins and let cool.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Set temperature back to 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: debest deboer brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, nuts, butter, egg and 1/2 of the milk together.
Divide and place about 1/2 of the mixture (just enough to cover bottom) in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with spatula.
Bake until slightly set, about 6 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit in colander, add sliced strawberries and pour all into a large bowl.
Add peach pie filling (you may want to cut peaches in pie filling into smaller pieces).
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Mix about half the cake mix (dry), peanut butter, oleo (margarine), eggs and water in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in peanuts. Place about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb deeply in center of each ball.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set in 375° oven.
Fill each center with jelly or preserves. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: crisscross bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; add garlic cloves.
Mix salt and cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours and then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Add the cucumbers, garlic cloves and salt after you drain.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pat into jars and process in water bath for 5 minutes.
(Pickles and juices are great for most salads also.)

title: grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts for 2 hours.
Grill until done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare and cube eggplant into casserole dish.
Add chopped onion, celery, green pepper and microwave until tender, drain.
Add oil, soup and cheese.
Add bread crumbs to cover top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°
or put in a crock pot on low for as long as you wish to simmer.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients alternately with all other ingredients.
We were never given any temperature but 325° to 350° and time according to size pans used. It was always baked in iron skillets in layers.
I make mine in loaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon together in one bowl. In another bowl mix oil and eggs well.
Pour this together with flour mixture and mix.
Now add all the other ingredients to flour mixture.
Bake in sheet cake pan or 3 layer pans whichever you prefer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken well in heavy pot with a little oil.
Add soup (cream of chicken soup can be substituted) and water to chicken. Add onion powder and seasonings.
Simmer for 1/2 hour, add carrots and cook until they are done.
Also you can add a chicken bouillon cube for added flavor; omit salt.
Serve over rice with cranberry sauce and a salad.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar to butter.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture to make a soft dough.
Roll out thin on floured board or cloth. Cut into cookies.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: homemade granola
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Lightly grease two 9 x 13-inch pans.
In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients, except dried fruit.
In another bowl, mix oil and honey.
Add to dry mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Sprinkle water over mixture one tablespoon at a time while stirring.
Put into pans and cook for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally until mixture turns light brown. Stir in fruit. Cook 15 minutes more until desired dryness.
Fruit should be soft still.
Cover and store.

title: mama's blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg yolks and water.
Mix well.
Add spices and soda to flour.
Mix jam and flour with other ingredients.
Add egg whites last.
Bake 45 minutes.
No temperature was given in this recipe.
I suggest 350°.

title: mexican green chili
directions: Cube pork, flour and fry until slightly browned.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add rest of ingredients and cook.
To thicken chili, add cornstarch.
This feeds 4 - 6 people.
Can be served over burritos, scrambled eggs, etc.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled to feed more people.

title: cranberry raspberry cheese mold
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water, stirring about 2 minutes.
Pour into blender.
Add cream cheese and blend on high until smooth.
Pour into 5-cup mold, sprayed with cooking spray.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, water, oil and salt.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
May add cheese for color.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Heat cream cheese and soup in top of double boiler until well blended.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in water and add with mayonnaise to somewhat cooled soup mixture.
Add to remaining ingredients and pour into oiled molds.
(Makes 1 large and 1 smaller mold.)

title: onion soup
directions: Slice 5 onions very thin.
Heat oil; melt 1/4 cup butter. Saute onions until golden brown. Do not burn. Deeper color gives better flavor.
In remaining butter, cook 1 whole onion on all sides.
Sprinkle with sugar and cook, browning on all sides. Add to sliced onions the broth, water and wine. Simmer 40 minutes. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove whole onion.
To serve, place in soup crock.
Float 1 slice of bread on top and cover with cheese. Broil until cheese melts.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla and cocoa. Boil 1 minute, rolling boil.
Add peanut butter, then add oats. Stir well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: peanut butter surprise
directions: Divide roll into nine sections.
Divide each 9th into 4th. Put 1/4 into tiny muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out and press peanut butter cup candy into each cookie.
Push candy in even with dough.
Lift out to cool.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: One stick of the butter should be very soft.
Mix it thoroughly with the powdered sugar, brown sugar, and peanut butter.
Press the mixture evenly into a 9 x 13 pan.
Melt the chocolate chips with the second stick of butter.
Gently pour the chocolate mixture over the mixture that is in the pan.
Refrigerate before cutting into small squares.

title: hamburger-potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and sage; pour half of meat into casserole.
Thinly slice potatoes and onion rings and layer half of them.
Over meat, layer
other half of meat, potatoes and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix tomatoes with melted butter and pour on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs; add fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Stir in sugar mixture; pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Set aside.

title: tea cakes
directions: Blend the sugar and shortening together with a fork.
Add eggs, vanilla and gradually add the flour, one cup at a time.
It will seem a little dry.
Spoon out on cookie sheet, ungreased, and bake in oven at 325° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown around the edges.
When you take them out, they will be soft, but as they cool, they will become firmer.
Do not overcook.

title: baked stew
directions: In Dutch oven or roaster with tight fitting lid, layer ingredients in order listed.
Do not stir.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
No browning necessary.
When done, the gravy is thick and brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
In greased baking dish, place half of potatoes.
Cover with half of sauce.
Repeat layers. Cover and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Shredded cheese may be added to top before baking, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with half the carton of Cool Whip.
Mix well. Fold in the rest of the Cool Whip and the pineapple and juice.
Add the marshmallows.
Chill.

title: swiss steak
directions: Put all ingredients (except steaks) together and mix well; bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, brown minute steaks and lay in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour on sauce and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: dill-shell macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Use more mayonnaise for smoother consistency.

title: crab spread
directions: Drain crabmeat very well and break apart with a fork.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir (do not use electric mixer) in crabmeat.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: alaskan sourdough starter
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Place in a warm place or closed cupboard overnight.
In the morning, mix well by hand and remove a 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Place in a scalded pint jar with a tight lid and place in the refrigerator for future use.
This is your starter.
The rest of the mixture can be used immediately for pancakes, waffles, bread or other recipes.

title: brownies
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt margarine.
Turn off heat and add cocoa; stir.
Add sugar; stir, then add eggs beaten well with vanilla; stir.
Add the dry ingredients (already sifted and measured).
Stir well.
If desired, add chopped pecans.
Pour mixture on well-greased and floured large cookie sheet pan with edges.
Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: hot spice drink
directions: Put brown sugar, cinnamon candies, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a coffee pot basket.
Pour juices and water into the coffee pot.
Percolate the mixture.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Let Cool Whip thaw.
Mix all 3 ingredients well with electric mixer using a large bowl.
Pour into 2-quart electric ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Recipe can be doubled for large freezers.
After freezing, let set about 30 minutes.

title: beefed-up biscuit casserole
directions: In large pan, fry ground beef, onion and chilies.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate biscuits into 10.
Pull apart each into 2 layers.
Press 10 biscuits over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup cream cheese (reserve remaining for topping), sour cream and egg; mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuit layers on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until deep golden brown.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Add sour cream and pineapple to jello mixture.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Top with marshmallows.
Chill 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth (1 minute).
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until edges are brown.
Sprinkle remaining chips over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes until shiny and soft. Spread.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: florentine dainties
directions: Combine eggs and sugar and beat until thick and lemon colored. Sift in flour and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoons, 2 inches apart, on a well-greased baking sheet. Bake in slow oven (325°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from baking sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: mock baby ruth bars
directions: Add the baking soda and corn syrup to the melted oleo or butter. Blend then add the oatmeal. Press firmly in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: date bread
directions: If pudding is in the mix, add 1/4 cup oil.
Beat 4 minutes.

title: minnie's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
This will make 2 pies.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package, substituting 7-Up for water.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds and refrigerate.

title: congealed salad
directions: Blend with mixer.
Put into bowl and place into refrigerator until jelled.

title: spicy applesauce mold
directions: Cook candies in 1 cup water, stirring frequently, until candies melt.
Heat to boiling; pour over gelatin in large bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in applesauce and vinegar.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with endive and orange slices of desired.

title: chocolate caramel candy(lucia pettit)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add the syrup and butter.
Continue to boil and add the vinegar as it starts to thicken.
While simmering, test for a soft ball in a cup of cold water and continue testing until it forms a thread (or tail).
When done, add the vanilla and immediately pour out onto a buttered 8-inch pie plate.

title: beefaroni
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in a greased pan. Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni in salted water and drain. Add to hamburger mixture and bake at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: busy day cheesecake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and pour into baked and cooled graham cracker crust. Can be topped with any variety of pie filling (cherry, blueberry or peach).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake one sheet at a time for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes and then remove to foil and cool completely.

title: mary elliot's raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let congeal until firm.
Add the berries and ice cream. Whip all to a froth.
Pour in baked pastry shell.
Let remain in refrigerator from 1 to 2 hours.

title: herring 'n sour cream
directions: Rinse and drain herring.
Combine all ingredients.
Marinate for up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 to 3 cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Pam a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add crushed pineapple. Layer cake mix over pineapple.
Cut 1/2 stick margarine in slices and place on top of cake mix. Add cherry pie filling and spread evenly.
Cover with rest of cake mix and rest of sliced margarine. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: country egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix real well.
Add vanilla.
Place in pie crust and bake until done. Beat egg whites.
Place on custard.
Bake until brown.

title: hamburger chinese style
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain fat and add soy sauce and green beans.
Bring to boil; simmer until tender.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Gently combine all ingredients except for crushed chips, cheese and margarine.
Combine these and sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato chip dip
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Serve chilled with chips.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in fat until onions are yellow. Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour, removing cover last 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan.
Add meat; brown both sides. Add hot water and salt.
Bring to a quick boil.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Add vegetables 30 minutes before meat is done; cook until tender, but not until it falls apart.
Season to taste.
Pour off liquid; measure and add hot water if necessary to make 2 cups liquid.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water by shaking in a small covered jar and add to liquid. Return liquid to stew and stir until it has boiled for 1 minute and is thickened.
Serve on hot platter or vegetable dish.

title: angel biscuits
directions: So the mixture won't bubble over the sides, use a small bowl or an 8 ounce cup to add one tablespoon of the sugar to the warm water.
Then add the yeast.
Mix well, then set aside until foamy.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix well.
Press in oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts over top.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Beat butter with mixer until creamy. Add flour, sugar and vanilla, beating until blended. Stir in pecans. Dough will be stiff. Shape into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack. Cool slightly and roll warm cookies in powdered sugar. Cool completely.

title: pickled eggs and red beets
directions: Hard boil eggs.
While boiling, drain juice from beets into small saucepan.
Add vinegar and sugar to beet juice.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer to keep warm while eggs finish cooking.
Immediately peel cooked eggs and place in bowl with red beets.
Pour hot juice mix over eggs and beets.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bring to room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in top of baked cake and pour mixture of milk and Coco Lopez over it.
Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Partially freeze beef; thinly slice across grain into 3-inch strips.
For marinade, combine soy sauce, oil, molasses, mustard, ginger, garlic and 1/4 cup water; mix well.
Add meat to marinade; let stand 15 minutes at room temperature.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.
Thread meat strips accordian-style on 12 skewers. Grill skewers over hot coals 5 to 7 minutes or to desired doneness.
Turn and baste occasionally with marinade.
Serves 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into Pyrex dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Cream next 3 ingredients with mixer. Spread over pretzel base.
Mix last 3 ingredients and let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over mixture and congeal.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix in order above and bake in a 9x13 pan at 350 degrees until golden brown. Cool and frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: harvest pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together
the
sugar,
flour
and
spices.	Stir in pumpkin
and molasses and melted margarine.
Beat eggs slightly. Add
the
cream
or
milk and add to the pumpkin mixture. Pour into
the
pie shell.
Flute or crimp high as filling is generous. Bake in hot oven (400°) about 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix ingredients and beat well.
Add raisins, if desired. Grease 2 one-pound coffee cans.
Pour 1/2 mix in each can.
Place double thickness of aluminum foil over each can and hold on with a rubber band.
Place on rack or towels in bottom of pan.
Fill with boiling water 1/3 way up cans and cover tightly.
Check occasionally to be sure there is water in pan.
Steam for 3 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda; stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Roasted, salted peanuts may be used, but omit salt and add peanuts after first 4 minutes of cooking.

title: rosy rocks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients, except oats, together into large bowl.
Add shortening, egg and soup.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (300 strokes by hand), scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.

title: tuna pickle delite
directions: Mix Tuna and Mayonnaise together.
Spread on bread and place on a cookie sheet.
Top with pickle.
Top with Cheese.
Melt under broiler.
Serve hot.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn out on cookie sheet.
Cool. Bring butter, sugar, salt and syrup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn; mix well.
Stir in peanuts if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate stars.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork in both directions across the top of the cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until light brown.
Place chocolate star in center of each cookie immediately after removing from oven.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix together and let stand (refrigerated) overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oktoberfest sausage
directions: Brown sausage in butter in Dutch oven.
Arrange remaining ingredients (except apple juice, salt and pepper) around sausage.
Top with apple juice.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir once.
Top with parsley.

title: cauliflower and broccoli bake
directions: Precook cauliflower and broccoli.
Heat together cream cheese, butter and celery soup.
Pour over top of vegetables that have been place on bottom of baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole with rice
directions: Boil 1 cup water with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add rice and onion. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until rice is tender.
Cut squash into 1/2-inch slices.
Boil 1/2 cup water with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Add squash and green pepper; cook about 5 minutes, until squash is tender.
Remove from heat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and squash to cooked rice; mix lightly.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Flake salmon. Combine all ingredients.
Place in well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: good broccoli casserole
directions: Can use cauliflower or California Blend.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Partly cook sausage and drain off fat. Place sausage in 2-quart casserole and cover with layers of rice, potatoes, onions and carrots. Add tomatoes with juice. Combine salt, pepper and sugar and sprinkle over top. Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serves 4.

title: a hearty eggplant sandwich
directions: On one slice of bread, layer eggplant, roasted red pepper, onion slices and chopped greens.
Add dash of oil and vinegar. Spread the remaining slice of bread with a generous serving of goat cheese.

title: frozen crescent rolls
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Cream the sugar, shortening and salt.
Add the eggs and mix.
Add 1/2 of the flour, then the milk and yeast mixture and mix.
Add remaining flour.
Knead on a floured board.
Put into a greased large bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk (about 2 hours).

title: popcorn cake
directions: Heat margarine, oil and marshmallows until melted.
Combine with popcorn, gumdrops and peanuts.
Pour into greased pan.
A tube pan works nice, too.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions, substituting fruit juice for milk.
(Do not use mandarin orange juice; it's too tart.)
Cool and add fruit (except bananas).
Just before serving, add bananas.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: tomato bread
directions: Heat tomato juice and butter together until butter is melted; add sugar, salt and ketchup.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water, stir to dissolve.
Add tomato mixture and 3 cups flour to yeast.
Beat by hand until smooth. Mix in remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Push down and divide in half.
Shape into loaves and place in greased pans.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: pretzel soup
directions: Blend flour with butter.
Add water to milk and heat.
Add blended butter and flour to diluted milk and stir until smooth and creamy.
Add a pinch of pepper and parsley.
Break as many pretzels as you wish into soup just before serving.
The amount of salt on the pretzels determines whether or not more salt should be added to taste.

title: breakfast squares
directions: Beat eggs lightly and blend with milk.
Pour in bread cubes and let soak about 10 minutes.
Spread sausage on greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Then add grated cheese and then bread crumb mixture. Mix in pan with spatula.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp mozambique
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Heat olive oil in a pan and saute shrimp until they start to turn pink.
Add garlic, bay leaf, salt, paprika and soy sauce.
Add lemon juice, white wine and 2 or 3 drops of Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with white or black pepper.
Add fresh parsley, if desired.

title: fruit tea
directions: Boil tea bags in 2 cups boiling water; drain.
Add sugar to tea; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: beaver lodges
directions: Lay out wax paper on which to cool your "lodges". Melt chocolate chips in a bowl in the microwave.
Stir in chow mein noodles or pretzel pieces.
Optional:
Add chopped nuts and/or raisins. Coat everything well with chocolate.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper to harden.
Shape, if needed (yields approximately 17 lodges).
For quicker hardening, place in freezer 5 minutes.

title: turkey and ham a la king
directions: Saute in 1/4 cup water the onion and green pepper until tender. Stir in flour and black pepper. Cook until smooth. Add broth and milk into mixture. Cook until thickened. Stir constantly. Stir
in turkey, ham and pimientos. Cook until thoroughly heated. Serve on plate with rice.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar, margarine or oleo and pecans. Press into oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° or just until brown; cool.

title: baked northern beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into small baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
After baking, allow to stand to absorb all flavors before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and sugar, being sure to mix well. Set aside.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, celery and grapes or oranges.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to chicken.
Toss well.
Chill several hours.
Serves 6.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and season to taste.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at low temperature for 45 minutes.
Garnish with red or jalapeno peppers.

title: gum drop bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Beat all ingredients except gumdrops and nuts in large bowl with mixer on low speed for 15 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 30 seconds. Stir in gum drops and nuts. Pour into pan.
Bake 60-65 minutes or until toothpick is inserted in center and comes out clean.
Loosen sides of loaf pan and remove from pan to wire rack.
Cool completely about two hours before slicing. For best results, wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours before slicing.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter into crumbs.
Set aside half of mixture. Mix molasses, water, soda, egg and 1/2 crumbs.
Put in pie shell and cover with the remaining crumbs.
Bake 11 minutes at 375° and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, onion, bell pepper and celery until red is gone and vegetables are transparent.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, chilies and mushroom soup.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add 3 cups of water and rice.
Cook until rice is done.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with raw vegetables.
Best if made 1 day before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: delicate thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat the first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Chill 10 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press center of each with thumb; fill with preserves.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, or until edges are golden.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Store, loosely covered.

title: silver cleaner
directions: Mix together; put into a large white-ware pitcher and pour on two quarts of water; stir until dissolved.
Then transfer mixture to clean bottles and cork them tightly.
Before using it, shake bottles well.
Pour some of the liquid into a bowl and wash the silver all over with it, using an old, soft fine linen cloth.
Let stand about 10 minutes and then rub it dry with a buckskin.
It will make the silver look like new.

title: chocolate smunchies(sugarless)
directions: Mix chocolate pudding according to directions on package, using skim milk.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix peanut butter with pudding. Drop 2 tablespoons onto each graham cracker square.
Place 1 tablespoons whipped topping on top of the mixture and cover with second graham cracker square to make sandwich.
Wrap and freeze. Yield: 35.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans and cover with 5 cups water; soak overnight.
(Or bring to boil; boil 2 minutes and cover.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.)

title: buttercup cheese straws
directions: Have cheese and margarine warm.
Mix well together.
Add flour, small amount at a time.
Add pepper.
Shoot with a cookie shooter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mango bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix flour and other dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg, then add applesauce.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well, then add raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are soft, moist cookies which keep well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Melt butter in rectangle pan. Pour in batter.
Pour in can of peaches with syrup.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let cool slightly before serving.

title: vegetable toss
directions: *Examples:
cabbage, zucchini, squash, green pepper, carrots and onion.

title: chocolate sundae dessert
directions: Combine crackers, nuts and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix peanut butter, chocolate syrup and corn syrup. Spread over crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Slice softened ice cream and place over chocolate mixture.
Freeze.

title: caldillo
directions: Brown round steak in fat until it is very brown.
Browning a long time makes a darker richer, broth.
Add garlic, onion and tomatoes.
Add 1 1/2 quarts water and salt to taste.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When meat is done, add cubed potatoes.
If desired, add chopped chiles.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Serve in bowls, since the Caldillo is very soupy.

title: fruit tart cake
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Pour over top 1/8 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in a casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top and add extra shredded Cheddar cheese, if you want.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with wire whip very well.
Spread on serving dish and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Then top with shredded lettuce, chopped onion, chopped tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: old-fashioned fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until done.
Add the other cup of water.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add orange juice and rind.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/8 thick.
Place cookies on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rice and veggie egg rolls
directions: In wok or large frypan, heat 1/4 cup vegetable oil until very hot.
(Careful not to burn oil.)
Working quickly, stir-fry onion and carrots for 3 minutes.
Add cabbage; fry until cooked down. Add garlic/chili sauce and mix thoroughly.
Add cooked rice.
Turn off wok or remove from heat.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Cool to room temperature.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of filling in center of egg roll wraps.
Wrap envelope style sealing end with flour/water mixture.
Fry in deep fryer or 1/2-inch deep oil in frypan, turning once, over high heat until golden.
Makes 20 to 24 egg rolls.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion; drain.
Stir in beans, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
In another skillet heat oil.
Quickly dip tortillas in hot oil just until softened.
Place 1/3 cup meat mixture on each tortilla.
Top with chopped tomatoes, roll tightly.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter, stir in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and enchilada sauce.
Cook and stir until boiling and boil 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: meat stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown sausage and ground round in a large pan with the onions, too.
Drain.
Cool.
Return to pan.
Cut tops out of green peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add tomatoes to meat and all but 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Mix together meats, cheese and tomatoes.
Stuff each pepper full of mixture (press down).
Add cheese to top.
Place each finished pepper in glass pan.
Add a little water (1/2-inch) to pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Mix jello and water and let cool; needs to be still liquid. Mix all other ingredients and pour into mold or flat dish.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes; add sugar and vanilla.
Take one large marshmallow; cover with sweet potatoes.
Roll in the crushed corn flakes.
Fry in butter.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: Combine egg, sugar, orange juice and margarine in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in biscuit mix.
Mix well.
Stir in orange marmalade and pecans; mix well.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full with batter.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes about 1 dozen.

title: 24 hour chicken
directions: Mix up the night before.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef and rice, onion, milk, salt and pepper. Roll into balls.
Place in baking dish.	Pour
soup
and water mix over balls.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no fail hot rolls
directions: Blend sugar, shortening and eggs.
Put yeast into 1/6 cup warm water.
Add all ingredients with half the flour.
Mix well and add rest of flour.
Let rise until double in size, knead and make into biscuits.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mango lime mousse tart
directions: Combine eggs, egg yolks and sugar in a stainless steel bowl. Whisk in the lime juice.
Set the bowl over a pot of simmering water and whisk the lime mixture continually for about 5 minutes until it is thick and mounds slightly.
Remove the bowl from the stove and let the lime mousse cool for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour the mousse into the tart shell.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour, until the filling is set.
Toss the mangoes gently into the rum.
Arrange mangoes in the tart shell, slightly overlapping, in a circular pattern.
Refrigerate the tart until ready to serve.
Serve with cream.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine water and raisins.
Bring to boil.
Cook at rolling boil about 3 minutes.
Drain raisins and reserve liquid.
Spread raisins on paper towel to drain.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of the warm raisin water.
Sift 6 cups flour into a large mixing bowl. Make a well in center.
Pour yeast mixture into well.
Sprinkle the 1 tablespoon sugar over yeast mixture.
Cover with towel and let rest 30 minutes.
Mixture should be bubbly.
Add eggs, oil, salt and remaining 1 cup sugar to yeast mixture.
Mix well.
If necessary, add enough water to remaining raisin water to make 1 cup.
(Mixture should be warm.)
Gradually add it to flour mixture. Add raisins.
With floured hands (dough will be sticky), turn dough out onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, working in more flour, if necessary to make a soft dough.
Place the dough into an ungreased bowl.
With fingertips, pat a small amount of oil over top of dough.
Cover tightly with damp cloth and let rise in warm place until indentation remains when fingertip is pressed into dough.
It will take dough more than 1 hour to double in bulk because it is heavier than conventional bread dough.
Thoroughly punch down dough.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise again until double in bulk, 45 minutes or longer.
Punch down dough.
Divide dough in three parts.
Roll each part on lightly floured surface into a rectangle, about 9 x 6-inches.
Divide cinnamon sugar into thirds and sprinkle over each rectangle.
Roll each rectangle, jelly roll fashion.
Place each roll in a greased loaf pan, 9 x 5-inches.
With fingertips, spread a thin coating of softened margarine over each loaf.
Sprinkle top with additional cinnamon sugar, if desired.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake about 25 minutes longer or until done.
(Dough also may be made into rolls in any desired shape.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain grease off.
Add pizza sauce and tomato sauce.
Let simmer while cooking macaroni.
Mix and pour into baking dish.
Cover with cheese and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: pepper corn
directions: Fry bacon and onion.
Drain off half the fat.
Add corn, tomatoes, green pepper and salt.
Cook for 15 or 20 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.

title: ham, potato and cheese casserole
directions: Make
a
cheese
sauce	and pour over ham and potatoes. Bake in	a
buttered
quart
casserole at 350° for 45 minutes. May be topped with buttered bread crumbs.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Simmer apple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt until thick. Stir in apples and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: mint candies
directions: Mash cream cheese; add flavoring and food coloring.
Mix in sugar; knead with hands until like pie dough.
Roll into marble size balls.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Press into candy molds. Unmold at once on waxed paper.
If you do not have a mold, flatten with hand on waxed paper.
Let sit for 24 hours until firm.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and pepper in plastic bag or bowl.
Stir chicken into eggs.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon and place in bag or bowl with baking mix.
Coat chicken.
Remove chicken.

title: lois' bacon wraps
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce in refrigerator overnight.
Drain chestnuts and roll in sugar.
Wrap chestnuts with 1/2 bacon slice and secure with toothpick.
Cook in microwave about 45 seconds for 8 wraps, turning and adjusting time as needed.

title: marinated mushrooms and peppers
directions: Clean and trim mushrooms.
In saucepan, combine vinegar and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Drain mushrooms; turn into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or longer.
Yields 1 quart.

title: overnight tossed salad
directions: Layer in order; don't stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simply bring milk, water and rice to a boil and boil 4 minutes (less if you cut recipe in half) or until rice is done and mixture is thick and creamy.
Stir often.
You can add raisins (couple hands full).

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans and press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes to golden brown; cool.

title: layered eggplant parmigiana
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Dip eggplant into beaten egg, then in flour mixture.
In large skillet, brown eggplant in hot oil and drain oil off eggplant.
Place in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, cutting slices to fit.
Sprinkle with half the Parmesan.
Top with half tomato sauce.
Repeat eggplant, Parmesan and tomato sauce and Mozzarella to create another layer.
Serve with French bread and salad.
Serves 4.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Mix everything except tenderloin in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place meat in dish and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning meat several times.
Drain, reserving liquid. Preheat oven to 325°.
Place meat on rack in shallow pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until meat reaches 170°.
Cool, wrap and chill.
About 30 minutes before serving, slice meat very thin. Place in chafing dish.

title: pea and crabmeat salad
directions: Toss together and serve.
May be refrigerated and served cold, also.

title: noodle and onion pie
directions: Blend ingredients with pastry blender and press into 9-inch pie pan.

title: baked haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Dip fish in milk.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Coat fish.
Put in a buttered baking dish and sprinkle with salt, pepper and thyme.
Pour melted butter or margarine on
fish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cooked fish with paprika.
Garnish with lemon wedge.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into deep dish pie pan or spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Mix.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheesecake and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oil and vinegar salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and be sure to shake well before using.
Keep this in a glass container in the refrigerator and it will last as long as the "store-bought" salad dressing.

title: beef bean combo
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in 12-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in green beans with liquid and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix the Good Seasons Italian dressing mix according to package directions, but omit the water.
Use only oil and vinegar, filling vinegar up to the water line, then add the oil up to the oil line on mixing bottle.
Add the sugar and mix well.
Then add 2 tablespoons of the mayonnaise into the mixing bottle and shake until mayonnaise is incorporated with the liquid.
Fold into shredded cabbage and carrots.
Fold in the remaining 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix together.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bar none cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While cake is hot, poke holes and pour Eagle Brand and caramel topping over the top. Let cool then top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crumbled candy bars over top.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over cut up chicken that has been placed in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
For easy clean up, line pan with aluminum foil.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: meat balls in sauce
directions: Mix together ground beef, onion, egg, salt and potatoes and shape in small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 4 to 5 minutes at 450°. Mix brown sugar, tomato sauce, lemon juice, garlic salt and wine. Simmer, uncovered, until thickened, about 20 minutes.
Add meat balls to sauce and let simmer.
Great for cocktail food or served over rice.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Add flour, salt and eggs.
Beat until almost smooth, then beat 2 minutes longer. Stir in whipping cream and vanilla until mixed well.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until top of filling is dark golden brown.
Serve warm or cooled.
Refrigerator is used for cool pie.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: italian green beans
directions: Mix together and cook.

title: chopped liver spread
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add liver.
Cook until pink (do not brown).
Cool.
Combine all ingredients and grind through food grinder.
Add enough boiling water to make fluffy and easy to spread.

title: gooey hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate, butter, half and half, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat. Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or pour into clean glass jar and seal tightly.
Store up to 6 months in the refrigerator.
Reheat before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: melissa's taco dip
directions: Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough water to finish 1 gallon.

title: fast fried rice for singles
directions: In a wok or nonstick skillet, heat oil and cook onions and carrots over medium heat until onions turn to a semi-clear color. Add green peas; stir until frost is off peas; add egg(s).
Stir. Add meat and rice.
Blend all ingredients together until everything is mixed well.
Add soy sauce to taste; mix well.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together in a bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Stir in the milk and melted shortening. Blend in the chopped nuts. Spread in 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with mixture of the brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour over entire batter the hot water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves warm. Makes 9 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put ingredients in blender
in
an
on-off motion for 1 minute or mix thoroughly by hand.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain off juice from apricots.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour; cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients, except bananas.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Add bananas just before serving.

title: tortellini carbonara
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the bacon, cream, parsley and cheese; cook until heated through.
Meanwhile, prepare tortellini according to package directions, drain and transfer to a serving bowl.
Drizzle cheese sauce over tortellini and toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: green vegetable dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend 4 minutes; refrigerate overnight.
Cut up fresh vegetables to dip in.

title: german festive cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.

title: jewel salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13 dish and let jell. Mix the sour cream, cream cheese and sugar. Combine and spread on the jelled salad. Let set. Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cream of any vegetable soup
directions: Put chopped vegetables and broth in a 3-quart pan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer until vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Puree vegetables and liquid in blender or food processor.
Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Add pureed vegetable/liquid.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and chicken soup in 9x13 pan. Mix flour, milk and margarine together and pour oven chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: caponata(eggplant appetizer)
directions: Wash and dry eggplant.
Leave unpeeled.
Cut in 1-inch cubes. Sprinkle with salt.
Add eggplant to a 12-inch skillet, heat 2/3 cup oil.
Stir often until browned and tender.
Drain on paper towel.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in a pan large enough to hold them in a single layer.
Do not brown meat.
Cut potatoes, carrots, onion and celery in chunks on top of meat.
Mix tomato sauce, water and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Then scatter tapioca on top.
Do not stir.
Seal tightly in foil; place in 350° oven for 2 hours.
You may turn down and hold for awhile.

title: you would be surprised if there's a bite left cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press in an oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown (approximately 1 hour).
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Let thicken.
Pour onto layer 2. Top with Cool Whip.

title: coated pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy. Add sugar, water and a little cinnamon. Melt margarine in pan in 200° oven. Pour pecans in bowl with egg whites and mix. Layer in pan with margarine. Check every 10 minutes until done.

title: caramel apple delight
directions: Blend all four ingredients together with a mixer until creamy. Serve with apple wedges.

title: honey crunch popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn and Chex cereal in large roasting pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and honey in small saucepan or in microwave and stir until smooth.
Drizzle this mixture over popcorn and cereal.
Stir to coat all pieces slightly.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: snack mix
directions: Melt margarine and add seasonings.
Mix and pour over crackers.
Mix well.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Mix molasses, brown sugar, water and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick on floured surface. Cut with floured cookie cutters.
Place about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until no indentation remains with touched, 10
to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Decorate.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and mash potatoes or mash with fork and leave partially chunked.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter and banana cookies
directions: Combine oats, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix peanut butter, margarine, sugar, brown sugar, bananas, egg and vanilla at medium speed.
Add to oats mixture.
Drop by 1/4 cup or scoop 5 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Spread with spoon about 3 1/2-inches wide.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Let cool. Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apple and sugar.
Let stand while preparing.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Sift together.
Stir all together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: maryland crab dip
directions: Mix all together; add some extra cheese on top.
Cook in 9 x 5-inch meat loaf pan at 350° for about 1/2 hour until browned and cheese is melted.
Eat warm.
Dip with wheat thins.

title: molded strawberry salad
directions: Combine pineapple and jello.
Heat until jello is dissolved. Cool in refrigerator until syrupy.
Add 2 1/2 cups buttermilk. Chill until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 6 hours.

title: ham and bean vegetable soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In 4-quart Dutch oven, combine beans and water. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 1 hour or soak beans in the water overnight in a covered pan; don't drain.
Bring beans and liquid to boiling. Add smoked hocks.
Reduce heat; simmer covered for 1 hour or until beans are nearly tender.
Remove hocks.
When hocks are cool enough to handle, cut off meat and coarsely chop.
Discard bones.
Add meat to pan along with remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add pineapple juice and chill.
Mix with chilled ginger ale in punch bowl.
Yield: 32 cups.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in a lightly greased 4-quart casserole. Place butter in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove mixture from oven.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir until coated.
Cook mixture on High 2 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Spread on waxed paper until cool.

title: broccoli dip
directions: In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine and saute onion. Melt the Velveeta (cut in chunks for easier melting).
Cook the broccoli according to package directions.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of minced garlic, dash of Tabasco, mushrooms and cream of mushroom soup; stir frequently.
Add broccoli.
Serve in crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup water with the cornstarch until you have a thin paste.
Combine 1 1/2 cups water and the sugar in the top of a double boiler and bring to a boil over direct heat.
Add cornstarch paste and cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Return to the double boiler and continue cooking until thick and smooth (about 15 minutes).
Pour in slightly beaten egg yolks; return to double boiler and cook for 1 minute longer.
Add lemon rind and juice and butter and blend well.
Cool and pour into a cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: *Add mint chocolate chips for mint flavoring.

title: easy frozen cukes
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand on counter for 2 hours, then drain.
Heat sugar and vinegar to dissolve sugar; cool.
Mix all ingredients and store in a refrigerator or in freezer.
Keeps quite a long time.
These are very good.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store tightly sealed in a plastic container. For tea, add boiling water to 2 teaspoons of mix for 1 cup of tea.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and beat 4 minutes with mixer at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until pick in center comes out clean.
Pie will puff then fall slightly.

title: ham spread
directions: Grind ham in meat grinder.
Add sweet relish and mix well. Add mayonnaise to make spreadable.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil until soft.
Stack; set aside.
Brown meat and add tomato sauce, chili and garlic powder to taste.
Simmer. Roll meat mixture in tortilla (you can secure with toothpick). Place stuffed tortillas in flat Pyrex dish.
Cover with tomato soup mixed with chili and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with sliced green peppers.

title: raisin pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the flour, baking powder and nutmeg together.
Add gradually and beat until well blended.
Stir in brandy.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan before removing to rack to cool.
Wrap and store for at least a week.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Grease 10-inch spring-form pan; dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Beat cream cheese and cottage cheese at high speed until creamy.
Blend in sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Reduce speed to low; add cornstarch, lemon and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add butter and sour cream on low.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges.
Turn oven off; let stand in oven 2 hours.
Remove, cool completely and chill.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine; add Bisquick, milk and Cheez Whiz. Bring to a boil until thick. Peel, slice, and season potato slices; place in baking dish. Pour sauce over potatoes. Bake for 1 1/2 hours (or less) at 350°.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook onion in butter until soft.
Add cheese; cook until cheese is slightly melted.
Combine broccoli, cooked rice and soup in oven-safe bowl.
Pour melted cheese over mixture. Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn au gratin in hash nest
directions: Press corned beef hash into a buttered baking dish to form a nest.
Combine corn, soup, onion and parsley.
Pour into nest.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: meatballs stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, pork, onions, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, eggs and milk in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Then, using a tablespoon shape into 1-inch balls. Place meatballs in ungreased flat 10 x 15-inch pan 1-inch apart. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, turning frequently, browning on all sides.
