Keep warm in 200° oven or store in freezer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and finely chop mushroom stems.
Place mushroom caps right side up on foil-lined broiler pan.
Brush tops of caps with 1 tablespoon oil.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes until tender; drain and set aside.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in medium skillet. Over high heat, cook and stir mushroom stems, red pepper and onion for 5 minutes or until almost dry.
Add French's creamy spread mustard and seasonings.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon vegetable mixture into each mushroom cap.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese evenly over caps. Broil for 5 minutes until lightly browned.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 appetizer servings.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Bake as directed in 2 round cake pans or a 9 x 13. When cake has completely cooled, slice layers in half, making 4 or 2 layers. Top with icing.

title: clay for baking and making ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add water, a little at a time, until you have a stiff dough.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface (7 to 10 minutes) until smooth and pliable.
Roll dough out to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters or make shapes and put together. Put hole in top of ornaments with straw or nail.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Drain zucchini for 1 hour and squeeze out water.
Mix all well and spread on greased pizza pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: baked filet of trout
directions: Melt butter. Grease a pan with margarine. Set up "assembly line" stations, then dip each fillet in melted butter, roll it in the bread crumbs and place the filet in the pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake muffin mix as directed.
Let cool.
Cook bacon and drain. Chop tomato, pepper and onion.
Put in separate bowl.
Crumble cooled cornbread in casserole dish.
Sprinkle beans with juice over cornbread.
Sprinkle onions and green pepper.
Spread Ranch dressing, then sprinkle tomato and crumbled bacon.
Can use 1 cup grated cheese between tomato and bacon.
Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.
(Can add more Ranch dressing before serving.)

title: hamburger balls in mushroom gravy
directions: Shape ground meat into 16 balls and brown in greased skillet. Add mushroom soup and simmer 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute shrimp and mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter for 2 minutes. Add soup and wine; blend well.
Spoon into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining butter, cheese and breadcrumbs. Sprinkle over shrimp mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls and press together on a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown; cool.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix with beater.
Put dab of margarine in hot frying pan. Put 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Flip when golden.

title: ham and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir quickly until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Layer half of potatoes, onions and ham in casserole dish.
Pour half of white sauce over potatoes.
Repeat layering.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fiesta fish and shells
directions: Have fish at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni. Drain.
Stir tomatoes, onion and taco seasoning together.
Add macaroni and green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Fold fish to fit into pan.
Spoon sauce over fish.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: apple-cranberry relish
directions: Put apple, orange and cranberries through food chopper.
Add sugar and walnuts.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes about 2 cups relish for serving with turkey, chicken or duckling.

title: bland brownies
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Combine milk, biscuit mix and eggs. Mix for 1 minute with electric beater.
Spread drained sausage in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with biscuit mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken (do not salt), pull off bone.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Take out enough to cover top of casserole, add onion.

title: pineapple bisque
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line a 14 x 16-inch pan with 1/2 of the wafer crumbs. Spread beaten mixture on this.
Add layer of drained pineapple. Spread Cool Whip evenly. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Add rest of crushed wafers as a crust.
Keep in refrigerator 12 hours before serving.

title: pitted bing cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries; bring juice to boil and add gelatin powder.
Mix the cream cheese, nuts, pineapple, cherries and cola together.
Add to gelatin in serving bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: alpine appetizer
directions: Combine cheeses, bacon and onion. Mix together beaten eggs and milk, then add to the cheese mixture. Mix lightly and pour into greased 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife comes out clean. Serve on stone ground crackers or small slices of rye bread.

title: homestyle chicken or tuna pie
directions: Line quiche pie pan with 1 crust.
Set aside.
Combine remaining
ingredients; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour filling in pie pan.
Top with second crust, seal and crimp edges. Split top of crust to vent.
Bake at 375° for 45 or 50 minutes or until brown.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter, melted, and pat into a 9 x 13 pan. Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs; beat until smooth. Spread over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening in saucepan.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Add sugar and mix well.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and salt together and add to chocolate mixture, 1/3 at a time.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad northwood
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth; toss with juice of lemon and cool.

title: blueberries jubilee
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer until thickened and clear.
Pour brandy over surface of simmering fruit.
Ignite with a long match.
Spoon flaming sauce over ice cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and nuts. Fold into Cool Whip; chill and serve.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat to boil.
Boil until it turns brown.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Put Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water and let set 1/2 hour.
When cooler, add pineapple, nuts, celery and cranberries (crush berries in blender).

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer all but soup and water.
Between each layer, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix tomato soup and boiling water.
Pour over top of the layers.
Bake in slow oven (250° to 300°), covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 5.

title: tomato yogurt soup
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender.
Add next 5 ingredients and process until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper and pour into bowl. Chill covered in refrigerator.
Garnish with additional yogurt and parsley.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread and leave for 20 minutes.
Add butter, raisins, crushed pineapple, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Mix well. Place mixture into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: golden ember sauce(barbecue chicken)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar or bottle.
Shake thoroughly. Let stand several hours before using.
Stir well before brushing on chicken.
Split chickens in half.
Brush generously on both sides with sauce.
Let stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Place on grill, hollow side down.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with sauce and turn.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender or brush with sauce often and turn chicken every 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned poor man's cake
directions: Boil all ingredients together except flour and baking soda. When cool, then add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Grease and flour any size pan, preferably loaf pan.
Pour contents in pans and bake in slow (350°) oven for approximately 45 minutes; let cool before cutting.
Cake can also be frozen for future use.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water together until it will form a hard ball when dropped in cool water.
Beat egg whites and salt at high speed for 3 minutes in a large bowl.
Pour syrup slowly into beaten egg whites while beating at medium speed.
Continue beating until mixture passes the glossy state.
Add nuts and vanilla and continue beating until it forms a peak when beater is raised. Pour on buttered platter or drop on waxed paper.

title: mamma's scrambled hamburger
directions: Combine water and onion and cook until tender.
Add beef and vinegar and cook until beef changes color. Pour off excess fat. Add tomato puree, A.1. sauce and salt to taste.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cheese slices may be added.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and add meat, garlic and onion and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 8 cups.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Defrost the spinach.
Squeeze out all excess water. Meanwhile, partially cook the pie crust (follow heating directions on package; about 10 minutes).
Next, heat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, mix half and half, 4 beaten eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg; mix.
Spoon in spinach and combine.
Sprinkle the cheese in the bottom of the partially cooked pie crust.
Then pour mixture into shell.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then lower heat to 350° and cook for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.l

title: new england corn chowder
directions: Brown salt pork until crisp.
When crisp, add chopped onions; try to remove pork.
Add flour and potatoes (make sure water covers potatoes).
Blend in flour.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, until the potatoes are done.
Add corn, milk and butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat well, but don't boil.
Add pork if you want to eat it.
Serve with parsley and paprika.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: flavorful eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water 5 to 8 minutes or until barely tender; drain well.
Brown beef in a skillet until done, stirring to crumble; drain well.

title: fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients except nuts until it forms a soft ball in a glass of water; remove from heat and add nuts.
Stir until it starts getting hard to stir; pour into greased pan to harden.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute; add sugar.
Mix well and add cinnamon. Use more if desired.
Add flour, vanilla and oil; mix well.
Fold in carrots (shredded) and walnuts or pecans.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: pecan bubble bread(overnight)
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Cover bottom with pecans.
Place cut up rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle dry pudding and cinnamon over the rolls.
Melt oleo and brown sugar; drizzle over the top.
Cover with towel.
Let stand on counter or in oven overnight.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes the next morning.
Invert on platter and serve.

title: poppy seed squash
directions: Place steamer basket in 1/2-inch water (water should not touch bottom of basket).
Place zucchini, yellow squash and jicama in basket.
Cover tightly and heat to boiling for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir in vegetables.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans in-a-hurry
directions: Mix beans, brown sugar, catsup, onion and mustard.
Place in a casserole.
Dot top with sliced bacon, diced.
Bake at 300° uncovered for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings overnight in all these ingredients, about 2 pounds of chicken wings.
Place on foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: busy day lasagne
directions: Cook rigatoni as directed; drain.
In bottom of 2-quart casserole or 9-inch square pan, pat a few spoonfuls of sauce. Arrange 1/2 of rigatoni in pan.
Cover with all of the cottage cheese.
Top with 1/2 the sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Arrange in layers the remaining rigatoni, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot pot
directions: Layer first four ingredients in casserole dish.
Do not stir. Cover.
Cook for three hours at 300°.
Forget about it and don't look at it during this time.
Remove from oven and add the mushrooms and wine.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake for another 1/2 hour, still at 300°.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: granny's corn light bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients; add buttermilk and mix thoroughly. Melt shortening (or oil).
Make sure sides of pan are covered lightly with oil.
Pour remaining oil into corn bread mixture and blend.
Bake in loaf pans at 375° for 55 minutes.
Especially good with barbecue.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in crust. Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg substitute and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour, baking soda and mix well. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape cookie dough into 1 inch balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press dough into 1/4 inch thick circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: beef and noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown the ground beef in a large skillet over medium high heat; set aside.
Cook macaroni according to package directions, drain and set aside.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, layer the macaroni, ground beef, tomato sauce and cheese, repeating two times.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until top layer of cheese is bubbly.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain. Add 4 cups of water, bouillon cubes, bell pepper, Ro-Tel, beans and cabbage. Bring to a boil and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: chili con carne or 10,000 volt chili
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Remove and brown meat. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, beer, salt, Tabasco and chili powder. Simmer 3/4 hour.
Then add beans and onions.
Serve over rice with French bread.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix all the ingredients by hand.
Make in rolls in wax paper. Place in refrigerator until thoroughly chilled.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello well with sugar.

Add pineapple. Heat over low heat. Bring to a boil until bubbly hot. Stir and set aside until cool. Then add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into dish or jello mold. Refrigerate until set.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
This sauce keeps well in refrigerator.
May be used with chicken or other meats.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat nutmeg, salt, sugar, oil, eggs and cinnamon.
Add and mix in order the pumpkin, water, soda, flour and nuts.
Grease well 2 loaf pans.
Fill 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool. Remove from pans.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sour cream and eggs well.
Pour batter in a slightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Take fork and swirl into batter, using back of fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: rose petal jam
directions: In a large saucepan, combine rose petals, 1 1/3 cups water, pectin and rose flower water.
Stirring constantly, bring to a rolling boil over medium-high heat.
Add sugar.
Stirring constantly, bring to a rolling boil again and boil 1 minute longer. Remove from heat; skim off foam.
If desired, tint with food coloring.
Pour into jars with tight fitting lids.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields about 1 pint jam.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Cream butter,
sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well. Stir in nuts and dates.	Chill 1 hour.
Roll into small balls. Bake on greased
cookie
sheets
at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain the first 4 ingredients into large bowl.
Add marshmallows and sour cream.
Chill overnight.
Enjoy!

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Put into a pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: grilled burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients; add beef and mix gently.
Shape into 10 patties.
Grill, uncovered, over medium coals for 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until meat is no longer pink.
Serve on buns with lettuce, tomatoes and onion if desired.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: relish
directions: Cook beets and peel.
Chop a head of cabbage and cook.
Add some horseradish (either fresh or canned).
Combine all of the ingredients in three desired proportions.
Pour over this equal amounts of vinegar and sugar.
Store in refrigerator and use as a relish with meats.

title: corn-on-the-cob(microwave)
directions: Shuck the ears of corn and wash.
Rub the butter on the corn (each ear).
Put in an 8 x 8-inch microwaveable bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix together with a whisk.
Pour into hot grease (about 1 inch), beginning in center of skillet and circling out.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and top with onions or cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta with rarebit sauce
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, in 12-inch skillet over high heat, into 10 cups boiling water, stir macaroni.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook until macaroni is done, stirring occasionally. Drain.
Return macaroni to skillet.
Over medium heat, heat drained macaroni, cheese spread, beer, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and ground red pepper until cheese melts and sauce is smooth, stirring frequently.
To serve, slice tomato. Arrange tomato slices over macaroni mixture. Garnish with parsley sprigs. Makes 6 servings.

title: quick "cut out" cookies
directions: Knead flour into dough. Between sheets of lightly floured waxed paper, roll dough about 1/4-inch thick. Freeze about 20 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 10 or 12 strips per half. Melt butter in a large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and tarragon. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add bouillon cube dissolved in hot water and lemon slices.
Stir to loosen any browned particles.
Cover and cook 2 or 3 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix well.
Chill, then roll into balls.
Put in freezer. (Makes about 100 balls.)
After thoroughly chilling, place balls on cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
A yummy snack.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let sit at room temperature about 2 hours to mix flavors.
Then add 2 1/2 cups tomato juice and 3/4 cup water. Chill.
Serve in bowls topped with sour cream, if desired. Refreshing on hot summer days.

title: christmas leftovers
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Layer ingredients starting with crumbs.
Pour the condensed milk over all the layers.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: victorian walnut cake(from the white house cookbook, 1887)
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter; add next 4 ingredients. Fill the cake pan with a layer of cake dough; add a layer of raisins upon the cake batter, then strew over these a handful of nuts and so on until the pan is 2/3 full.
Line the tins with well-buttered paper.
Bake in a steady, but not quick, 325° to 350° oven.
This is most excellent.

title: carrot fritters
directions: Peel or scrape carrots, trimming both ends.
Cut lengthwise into halves or in quarters, depending on size.
Cook covered, in salted water with a teaspoon of sugar, until fork tender.
Drain. Place in a baking dish and sprinkle with brown sugar* and bake in oven at 400° until nicely glazed, about 15 minutes. Serve.

title: grape wine
directions: Mix and pour into plastic gallon jug.
Fill almost full with water.
Place
a
large balloon on top.
Let stand until balloon blows up, about 3 weeks, then goes down.
The wine is ready.

title: peanut butter-butterscotch pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Blend well.
Put into a graham cracker crust and put meringue on top. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and margarine for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows, chocolate bits and nuts.
Stir until melted and mixed.
Pour into large, well-greased pan.
Cool and cut.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Then put on chicken.
Put in oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber slices
directions: Bring to boil.
Remove from stove and let cool.
Wash and slice cucumbers.
Place in containers.
Pour syrup over cucumbers, allowing enough room to expand in freezer.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Unroll crescent dough and pat 1 package into bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Spread over dough in pan.
Pat remaining dough over cream cheese mixture. Beat egg whites slightly and brush some of the whites over the pastry.
Mix together remaining 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Sprinkle or spread over top crust; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: western skillet noodles
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add water and bring to boil.
Add noodles and sauce.
Cook for 7 minutes.
Add chili powder and corn.
Heat through.
Add cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Fill each cup with broth.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight.	Remove from fridge one hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: sweet potato pie(over 50 years old)
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust. Cook in a hot oven for about 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Cooked shrimp may be used instead of fresh shrimp.
Split shrimp and season with salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Melt oleo. Add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly, uncovered, until onions are wilted.
Add seasoned shrimp and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to mixture.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: maple frosting
directions: Combine Crisco, salt, syrup and vanilla and add 1 cup sugar. Add milk and remaining sugar.
Alternately mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add and blend well the pineapple and zucchini.
Combine remainder of ingredients.
Stir into zucchini mixture until well blended.
Pour mixture into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 5 or 6 small loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately one hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
(Small pans will take approximately 45 minutes.)

title: crab appetizer
directions: Place block of cream cheese on plate.
Cover with drained crab meat (lightly mashed with fork so crab stays in place).
Pour chili sauce over all to cover.
Serve with crackers, cutting straight down to get some of everything to put on cracker.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix ingredients, except chocolate chips; press in pan.
Melt the chocolate chips.
Add enough melted butter to make it shiny and spread on top.

title: egg noodles
directions: Add lard, cream, salt and baking powder to egg yolks and mix well.
Add enough sifted flour to make a soft, non-sticky dough that will roll thin, about the consistency of pie dough.
These can be cooked immediately.
Can also be made ahead of time.
Be sure they have plenty of flour on them to keep them from sticking together.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower, apples and celery in small pieces.
Combine all with peanuts.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt
1 stick of butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs into the butter.
Mix well and pat down.
Sprinkle on this 1 can coconut.
Over this sprinkle butterscotch
chips.
Then
sprinkle on broken nut meats.
Pour on Eagle
Brand condensed milk.
Cook in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool
before
cutting
into
squares.
Makes 20 to 25 squares.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sweetener, baking powder, salt, berries and margarine.
Add egg and milk.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 15 medium size muffins.

title: chocolate and pear bread pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat cream cheese, the 2/3 cup sugar, lemon peel, vanilla and the 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and cinnamon with an electric mixer on low speed until smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating just until combined after each addition.
With a large spoon, stir in milk or cream, bread, pears and chocolate.

title: cranberry-cottage cheese mold
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Break up the cranberry sauce in a bowl.
Sieve the cottage cheese or, preferably, puree it in a blender.
Put half the cooled gelatin mixture in the cranberry sauce and the other half in the sieved cottage cheese.

title: fruit cake
directions: *Mrs.
C. C. Grider uses 4 eggs.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion and pepper.
Cook until onion is clear.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven until hot.

title: whole cranberry bread
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Add and mix cranberries and walnuts thoroughly to cook.
Heat orange juice.
Add shortening and egg.
Blend into dry ingredients, mixing until just blended.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
Remove from pan to cool.
Flavor improves if bread is stored one day.
Colorful dish for the holidays.

title: aunt margaret's banana bread
directions: Add first 4 ingredients, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour, soda, nutmeats and salt and stir with a spoon.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Crumble hash browns.
Add all ingredients, except fried onions.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour. During the last few minutes of cooking time, pour the fried onions on the top.

title: helen's hungarian cheese
directions: Cream the cream cheese, Cheez Whiz and butter.
Then add the mustard, caraway seeds and chives.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight or the seeds will be hard and taste like wood chips. Spread on buffet style rye bread, rye crisps or crackers.
Best way is spread on real crusty Jewish rye bread.
If you're lucky enough to live in parts of the country where you can get it!!
This recipe makes A LOT!!!
You can halve the recipe and still have enough for a small party.
Enjoy!

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut first 3 ingredients into bite size; mix together. Mix sugar, Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add to fruits.
Chill and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cream cheese, butter, and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, creaming mixture after each egg.
Add flour slowly.
Pour into 12 c. bundt pan or angel food pan.
Bake at 350 for 1-1/2 hours.
Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sweet green pea casserole
directions: Drain peas; place in bottom of baking dish.
Add on top of peas, onion, pimentos and cheese.
Repeat second can of peas, onion, pimentos and cheese; salt and pepper to taste (usually very little).
Pour the cream of celery soup over the ingredients. Sprinkle on top the buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and crumbs are browned.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: five hour oven stew
directions: In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, place the stew meat down the center length of the dish.
Cut potatoes, carrots, green beans, onions and celery or whatever other vegetables you like in your stew on either side of the beef stew meat.
Mix together sugar, salt and tapioca.
Sprinkle over top of meat and vegetables.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup to 230°.
Add peanuts.
Boil to 310°.
Remove from heat and add butter, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and spread on buttered pan to cool.
Cool and break.

title: carey's au gratin potatoes
directions: Dice and boil potatoes.
Melt 12 tablespoons of butter and blend in flour; gradually stir in cream until thickened and boiling.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Pour half of cream over potatoes; add 1/2 of cheese.
Pour over remaining cream and add last of cheese.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter and blend in crumbs. Sprinkle over top and bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Remove and discard visible fat from oxtails.
Parboil oxtail for 5 minutes; drain.
Add new water and all ingredients except mustard cabbage and togan.
Simmer for 2 hours or until oxtail is tender.
Remove scum.
Remove green onion and celery.
Add togan and cook until soft.
Add salt to taste.
Add mustard cabbage. Serve soup garnished with chopped green onion and Chinese parsley. Use finely grated ginger and shoyu as dipping sauce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli in bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix onion, mayonnaise, vinegar together and then pour over broccoli.
Mix in bacon and cheese.
Can also add half cauliflower, half broccoli, and carrot for color.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Combine the tomatoes, water, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 X 9 inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: fluffy pink salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Garnish with cherries and extra pecans.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Do not double.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas cocoa
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well. To serve, combine 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 cup hot water. Top each serving with marshmallows and use peppermint or cinnamon stick to stir. Make 4 quarts.

title: julie's strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Tear cake into chunks and put into Bundt cake pan or mold. In a separate bowl, dissolve Jell-O and 1 cup boiling water. Measure strawberries and add water to equal 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O and mix.
Pour mixture over cake in pan.
Refrigerate until solid. Unmold and garnish with Cool Whip.
A light dessert.

title: speedy shepherd's pie
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, cook beef over medium heat, stirring with wooden spoon to break up meat, 3 to 4 minutes, until no longer pink.
Add onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, until onion is soft, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add carrots and peas.
Continue to cook and stir until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.
Add broth. Bring mixture to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Let simmer until most of the liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Transfer mixture to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with prepared potato flakes, spreading and fluffing with a fork.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: august cooler
directions: Pour 1/3 cup orange juice into a large drinking glass or mug. Add 1/3 cup cranberry juice cocktail, 1/3 cup pineapple juice. Stir well.
Add 1 scoop orange sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and beat.
Mix in bananas and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup and milk. In shallow casserole dish, arrange broccoli and chicken.
Top with soup mixture.
Add Cheez Whiz as desired (about half a jar to almost cover) and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Broil about 1 minute to lightly brown topping.
Makes 4 servings.

title: miracle whip
directions: Beat thoroughly in a blender the oil, egg and water to make one cup, lemon juice, dry mustard and salt. Cook the flour, water and vinegar in a sauce pan. Bring to a boil, then blend into first mixture. Beat hard until smooth.

title: tangy marinated pork chops
directions: In a screw top jar, combine all ingredients, except pork chops. Shake well. Place chops in a heavy plastic bag, then place in baking dish. Pour marinade carefully into plastic bag. Fasten bag with twist tie. Make certain to squeeze.
Marinate 8 hours in refrigerator; turn bag occasionally.
Drain chops. Reserve marinade. Place chops on rack in broiler pan. Boil 3 to 5 inches from heat for 10 to 13 minutes, basting with marinade.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Use double boiler.
Mix ingredients together.
Put on wax paper and put in freezer overnight.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
Spoon into loaves on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and slice.
Spread pieces on side and bake at 450° for a few minutes to brown.

title: christmas pudding(plum pudding)
directions: Sift flour and spices together into large mixing bowl.
Add next 13 ingredients and stir until well combined; stir in eggs. Simmer molasses, brandy, orange and lemon juice and stir into mixture until well combined.
Divide into 2 ovenproof bowls, if possible, with lids or cover with double layer of buttered wax paper then foil.
Tie string around edge of bowl to secure.
Place inside large pan and pour in boiling water to reach 3/4 way up of each mold.
Cover and steam over medium heat for 5 hours.
Most people in Britain make their Christmas puddings in October long before all the other preparations begin.
In our family, we all took a turn in stirring the mixture and making a Christmas wish at the same time.
Store covered in cool place.
Do not freeze.
To reheat, steam for two hours before heating.
Serve with whipped cream or English custard.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla, melted margarine, pecans and coconut.
Pour mixture into pie shells and bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: haystacks
directions: Dissolve butterscotch chips in oil. (Do not overcook.) Add noodles and marshmallows. Spoon on wax paper. Sprinkle with nuts. Let cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternately with egg blended with vinegar and vanilla.
Shape dough into balls, place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash balls flat with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: something on a bun
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on hot dog bun halves. Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Very tasty for lunch or late snack.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Blend flour, margarine and one-half cup chopped nuts; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and one cup Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Make one large box of instant pudding according to package and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled and a second casserole frozen.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening
and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Add
combined dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir in chips and
nuts.	Drop from teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at
for	10
to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Serves 4 but easily doubled.
Just increase cooking time a little.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix milk, sugar, Karo syrup and pecans and boil to 240° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from the heat.
Cool to lukewarm and add butter and vanilla.
Beat lightly until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
You must work fast taking it up so it will look smooth.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread with 2 tablespoons butter, place upside down in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Saute onions, mushrooms, green and red pepper, ham or bacon bits in 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over bread.
Dust cheese with flour and sprinkle over.
Whisk eggs, add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes until fluffy and brown at 375°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts on sheet of wax paper.
Pound slightly with mallet, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in a large skillet.
Put chicken in and cook over high for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer or they will be overcooked and dry.
Transfer to warm serving platter.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Drain limas.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding ginger ale just before serving. Freeze some punch in ice cube trays and add to punch to keep chilled without diluting flavor.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain and add layer of Tater Tots. Add cream of chicken soup and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes. Mushroom soup may be substituted for chicken soup.

title: maple lace cookies
directions: Boil maple syrup and butter together for 1/2 minute.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by small teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Allow at least 3 inches between cookies.
They spread.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet for 30 to 60 seconds and remove very carefully, using an upside down spatula.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.
They do not freeze well.
Store warm and dry.

title: lasagna deluxe
directions: Crumble ground beef into large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until onion is tender; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, undrained mushrooms, parsley flakes, basil, oregano, red pepper and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook noodles using package directions; drain.
Mix egg with cottage cheese in bowl.
Spread 1/4 of the meat sauce in 7 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool for 20 minutes.
Place on cake plate, dust with confectioners sugar or drizzle confectioners sugar with orange juice over cake.

title: easy mock shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with 1/2 of chili
sauce and onion, using electric beater.
Add more sauce if necessary.
Use chips to dip!

title: pumpkin supreme
directions: Preheat gas oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs and 3/4 cup of the sugar.
Add margarine; mix well.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining sugar, cream cheese and eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Pour over crumb crust.
Bake 20 minutes; cool.

title: chili-cheese bake
directions: Spoon 1/3 of the chili onto bottom of a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Arrange 1/2 the crackers over chili.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese and onion. Repeat layer. Top with remaining 1/3 chili.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cookies(45 years or older)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Add cinnamon and cloves; mix well.
Blend in fruit cocktail, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
With teaspoon, dip out batter and drop onto cookie sheet in balls.
Heat oven at 375° and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
(Makes about 2 dozen.)

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using a large skillet brown meat in butter. Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer
30 minutes.
Stir in onion and bell peppers.
Cover and cook 5 more minutes.
Blend corn starch, water and soy sauce together.
Pour over meat.
Cook until the sauce is clear and thick, about 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hawaiian cold slaw (diet)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This is very good and very low in calories.

title: old fashioned pan rolls
directions: Early in the day or up to 1 week ahead, in a large bowl combine sugar, salt,
yeast
and
cups of flour.
In a 1-quart saucepan,
over
low
heat,
heat water and 1/2 cup of butter until very
warm (120° to 130°, butter does not need to melt).

title: tomato conserva(miscellaneous)
directions: Remove cores from the plum tomatoes and cut in half.
Slice garlic thin and press into tomato halves.
On an oven proof pan, coat the tomatoes with the olive oil, salt and pepper.
Place in a 350 degree oven.
Roast the tomatoes until they are slightly brown and soft.
This will take approximately 15 - 20 minutes.
In a stainless steel bowl, mix the remaining ingredients and stir.
Add in tomatoes and mix with a fork to break up the tomatoes and infuse the flavor.
This recipe can be used on grilled salmon, but can also be used for pork or chicken.

title: apple butter
directions: Fill your crock-pot 3/4 full of applesauce.
When it's hot, then add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook on high several hours. Keep dipping off the excess liquid that you will find laying on top.

title: hot salsa
directions: Mix together in blender until well chopped the tomatoes, onion and jalapeno peppers.
Melt the Velveeta cheese in a bowl in the microwave oven.
Add the tomato mixture and microwave until hot. Keep stirred to prevent lumps.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat into 1 to 2-inch squares.
Roll in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Brown meat on all sides.
Cover with 1 quart of water.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 2 hours (add water as needed).
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 30 minutes. Add macaroni or noodles, if desired.
Cook until tender.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.
Gets better each time it is reheated.

title: lentil vegetable soup
directions: Heat olive oil in 6 to 8-quart pot over medium heat.
Add green peppers, onions and garlic.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes until vegetables are soft.
Add broth, water, lentils, carrots and potatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in spinach and kielbasa. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes until lentils and spinach (if frozen) are thoroughly cooked.
Makes 16 cups.

title: meat balls with spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until golden.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook slowly 1 hour.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in bowl.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar to yolks.
Add chocolate to sugar and yolks.
Fold in egg whites slowly.

title: onion-mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: double decker pumpkin pie
directions: Using wire whisk, mix 1 tablespoon of milk and cream cheese. Mix until creamy.
Mix Cool Whip into cream cheese
mixture.
Lay in bottom of pie shell.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in glass bowl.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes on High.
Mixture should be bubbling and peanuts browned.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer. Add soda; stir until foamy.
Pour onto greased baking sheet. Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cut sweet potatoes and boil until tender. Cream potatoes until smooth, then add butter, eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk and vanilla. Mix well after adding each ingredient. Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350°. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and spread evenly in 9x13 greased pan.
Combine cheese and cornflakes and sprinkle on top.

title: banana cream cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine cracker crumbs and sugar. Stir in butter. Set aside 1/2 cup for topping. Press remaining crumb mixture onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan or a 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix cheeses and nuts together and shape into rolls.
Roll in chili powder and chill.
Serve on crackers or chips.

title: baked cod
directions: Dredge codfish in French dressing. Coat with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or just until flaky. Do not overcook.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat through.
Serves 2.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Cook eggs, flour, pineapple juice, sugar and salt until thick; cool.
Combine this mixture and macaroni, rinsing macaroni before mixing.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add 20 ounce pineapple chunks (which were drained).
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: fish baked in sesame sauce(samak bi tartour)
directions: Clean and salt fish.
Rub with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 15 minutes until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Gradually stir lemon juice and water into tahineh. (If tahineh in can is separated into oil and thick paste, pour into blender.
Blend until smooth and return to the can.
It stays smooth for a few months.) Fry onion in 3 tablespoons oil until yellow and pour the tahineh sauce and onion over the baked fish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 5.

title: mexican chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute onions in vegetable oil; add to meat.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook for 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: wedding cake frosting(for standard cake)
directions: Cook the milk and flour, stirring constantly, until thick. Mix the Crisco, sugar and vanilla; whip until fluffy (test to feel for sugar).
When milk is cool (must be cool, or it melts), mix the two together.
Frost a 1, 2 or 3 layer cake.

title: rocky road fudge pops
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, combine pudding mix and milk. Microwave, uncovered, on high for 6 to 7 1/2 minutes or until bubbly and slightly thickened, stirring every 2 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes, stirring several times.
Meanwhile, combine peanuts and chocolate chips; place about 2 tablespoons in each cup.
Stir marshmallow cream into pudding; spoon into cups.
Insert sticks and freeze.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, oats, salt and pepper; shape into six patties.
Place in a baking dish.
Dilute soup with water; pour over patties.
Bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan; spread evenly.
Dump cherry pie filling and spread evenly. Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over cake mix.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: noah's microwave no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in large microwave safe bowl.
Add margarine and milk.
Cook 4-5 minutes on high or until boiling. Stir and cook 1 1/2 minutes on high.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, and then oats. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let set.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix yellow squash, onions, peppers and salt; mix well.
Put in a crock pot.
Cover with water, then with ice.
Let set 3 hours. Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drain squash and add vinegar mixture.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: nelma's pepper steak
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in small amount of grease. Add steak and cook until white.
Add beef broth, water, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until done. Thicken gravy with cornstarch.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add jello to hot water.
Grind all ingredients.
Add sugar. Mix all together.
Pour in dish and chill until firm.

title: italian supper casserole
directions: In a medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat. Add Sloppy Joes mix, then add tomatoes with juice.
With a spoon, cut tomatoes into large pieces.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together and cook at 350° for 40 minutes in a casserole dish with 1/4 stick of melted butter.

title: broccoli gourmet
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted boiling water, drain well. Combine soup, sour cream, eggs, onion, salt, cheese crackers and cheese.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with about 2 tablespoons crushed cheese crackers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, then add 2 eggs, chocolate chips, walnuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Add to creamed mixture the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Roll into golf ball size and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes and cookies should be moist.
Makes about 42 cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, peanut butter and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.

title: cashew crunch
directions: Put all ingredients into heavy skillet.
Stirring constantly, boil until light brown.
Cashews will look toasted.
Pour out onto cookie sheet.
When cool, break into
pieces.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Combine eggs, oil, strawberries and juice.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fast blueberry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and shape around graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: snowball dessert(serves 15)
directions: Beat buttermilk with whipped cream.
Add pineapple and pecans. Add vanilla.
Place in Pyrex and freeze for 24 hours.

title: dream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sandra's strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil the water, sugar and cornstarch.
Add strawberry jello.
Add strawberries.
Pour into prepared pie crust.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fill a greased baking dish with vegetables, turkey, bread cubes, gravy and seasonings.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, oleo, syrup and salt to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda; mix well with popped corn.
Spread in two shallow buttered cake pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: easy deer chili in crock-pot
directions: Add onion, jalapeno peppers,
pinto beans, deer meat or hamburger,	 tomato
sauce,
chili
powder,
lemon
juice, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Add
enough
water to cover, about 4 inches in crock-pot.
Cook on high, 4 to 5 hours.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 4-quart ice cream maker.

title: fresh mushroom soup(lo-fat)
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan. Add onion and stir over medium heat until onion is translucent. Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Blend in flour until vegetables are well coated. Add stock slowly, stirring constantly. Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add white pepper, nutmeg, cream cheese and milk.
Stir until cheese is melted and milk is warmed through, but do not boil.
After placing in individual serving bowls, garnish with fresh herbs.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Mix next 3 ingredients in small bowl. Mix well and pour over ingredients in large bowl. Mix; refrigerate 2 hours, mixing occasionally.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix the vegetables.
Then pour all the other ingredients over the vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: quick as a wink salad
directions: Combine jello, straight out of box, with crushed pineapple in a casserole bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish the top with mandarin oranges.
Chill in refrigerator for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups chicken broth until done (5 minutes). Saute onion, pepper and celery. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes until browned.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended. Spread on fresh bread.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and carrot.
Cook until onion is tender, not brown.
Cook beef in skillet until meat is crumbly; drain.
Add meat to vegetable mixture.
Stir in tomato juice, potatoes and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine flour with a cup of milk and beat until free of lumps; stir into soup mixture.
Add remaining milk and heat, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.

title: apricot cheese delight
directions: Drain and chill fruit.
Mix Jell-O using water and fruit juices. Let cool. Add fruit and marshmallows. Chill until firm.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar. Let stand until juicy. Mix in flour and egg yolks, fold in 2 beaten egg whites. Pour into uncooked shell. Bake 425° for 10 more, reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a blender, place beans and salsa.
Blend until smooth. Spread in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with green chilies and pimientos.
Wash blender and place cottage cheese in blender; blend until smooth.
Spread cottage cheese on top of bean mixture in pie plate.
Cover and chill for at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle with tomato and Cheddar cheese on top of cottage cheese layer. Serve with tortilla crisps or vegetables.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan and boil 1/2 minute.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients except spaghetti in large pot.
Add enough water to thin.
Bring to boil.
Break spaghetti in half and add.
Lower heat and simmer until spaghetti is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse corn meal.
Reserve 1/2 cup of crumb mixture for top.
Blend in baking soda; stir in sour milk and eggs.
Put 1/2 of batter into greased and floured large flat pan.
Spread mincemeat over batter.
Sprinkle with crumbs and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in chafing dish or skillet.
Blend in flour. Gradually stir in cream.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Stir in small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add lobster; heat.
Add cooking sherry and lemon juice.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve on toast points.
Serves 4.

title: aunt naomi's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs and juice from fruit cocktail; mix well.
Fold in fruit cocktail.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients; blend well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: zwieback custard dessert
directions: Mix the sugar, cinnamon, and margarine with the crushed zwieback biscuits, set aside 1 cup of the mixture.
Line a 9x13-inch dish with the remaining crumb mixture and bake until golden brown (about 10 minutes) at 350°.

title: date macaroons
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla and almond extracts until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut, dates and almonds.

title: chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until well done.
Then add 1 package hot chili mix and 1 package mild chili mix.
Remove excess liquid.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Rinse and drain the purple hull peas.
Clean seeds from jalapeno and dice.
Seed and dice all other ingredients and mix in bowl.
Salt and pepper.
Squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over it; mix.
Add cooking oil.

title: new england brown bread
directions: Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour in greased tin.
Cover tightly.
Steam for 3 hours.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Grind ham and cheese in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients, except cereal.
Cook noodles per package directions; drain.
Add ham and cheese mixture to noodles; stir to mix.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with crushed cereal and return to oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: meat marinade
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place the meat for your cookout or oven in a shallow dish.
Cover with the marinade (makes about 1 1/2 cups).
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Grill or bake meat.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer in order and refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff 2
directions: Roll beef in flour.
Brown in butter.
Add onion when meat is almost brown and finish browning together.
Remove onion to a bowl.
Add broth, seasonings and mushroom juice to meat mixture. Cover and simmer 45 minutes or cook in pressure pan for 15 minutes.
Add flour to water and stir to make a paste.
Add paste slowly to the meat mixture.
Stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and add cooked onion, the mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat again, but do not boil.
Serve over rice, noodles or spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: great chocolate shake
directions: Blend ingredients together in a blender for 2 to 3 minutes or until well blended.

title: great aunt helen's cornmeal mush
directions: Mix cold water and corn meal.
Stir in boiling water and salt. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Cover, continue cooking over low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Chill until firm (overnight is best).
Slice and fry crisp.
Serve hot with syrup or try a tablespoon of sugar dripped with creamed coffee.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: Note:
Need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.

title: balloon balls to make with a pop!
directions: Blow up balloon until it is 2 to 4 inches in diameter.
Mix 3 parts glue with 1 part water in small bowl.
Dip floss or 1/8-inch wide ribbon into glue mixture, stripping out excess with fingers. Wrap floss or ribbon around balloon until a secure webbing is formed.

title: bread machine beer bread
directions: Heat beer with honey, margarine and water (90° to 105°).
Add to dry ingredients.
Place machine on manual setting.
Remove from machine when it beeps and shape dough into a round loaf.
Place on greased cookie sheet, baking pan or casserole.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until it sounds hollow when tapped.

title: grape pie
directions: Blend together the sugar, flour, tapioca and cinnamon.
Add the grapes; toss gently.
Allow to stand for about 15 minutes. Line a pie dish with a standard crust.
Pour grape mixture into crust; dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover with lattice top crust strips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about an hour, or until golden.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook sausage (pieces) and onion in a 3-quart saucepan until sausage is light brown.
Drain grease; stir in tomatoes with liquid, beans, broth, water and zucchini.
Break up tomatoes with wire whisk.
Heat to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until zucchini is tender.
Sprinkle each individual portion with cheese.

title: dip for nacho chips
directions: Spread bean dip in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with guacamole.
Mix together sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning and lay on top of guacamole.
Chop green onions, tomato, olives and cheese. Mix together; put on last layer.
Use round nacho chips for dipping.

title: dump cake
directions: Stir twice daily until the 30th day.
You are now ready to share your recipe and make your Friendship Cake.
Drain off the juice and give six of your friends 1 1/2 cups each and a copy of this recipe so they can make their own Friendship Cake.
The fruit remaining will make 3 Bundt or three large loaf cakes.

title: punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, pour Hawaiian Punch, ginger ale, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Stir together and chill. Right before serving, add sherbet.

title: chex honey roast mix
directions: Microwave Directions:
Prep time is 10 minutes.
Cook time is 5 minutes.
In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt margarine on High 45 seconds.
Stir in honey.
Gradually add cereal, nuts, apricots and raisins, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated. Microwave on High 4 minutes, stirring every minute.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine; mix sugar, flour and milk until smooth.
Add margarine; place peaches in bottom of dish (1 1/2 to 2-quarts). Pour mixture over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown minute steaks and onions in pan.
Add garlic salt and cook 5 minutes.
Combine soup, sour cream, mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over steaks and onions.
Serve on hot noodles.
Serves 6.

title: potato planks
directions: Set oven control
to broil.
Cut each potato lengthwise into eights.
Place
potatoes,
cut
sides
down, in ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch; brush with oil.
Mix remaining ingredients;
sprinkle
potatoes
with
half
of the mixture. Broil potatoes
with
tops	about 3-inches from heat until potatoes begin
to	bubbly	slightly,
about 10 minutes. Turn; brush with oil and sprinkle with remaining salt mixture. Broil until golden
brown
and tender, about 5 minutes longer. Sprinkle with snipped parsley or Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: *Green or Granny Smith apples are good for this recipe.

title: oma's blueberry cobbler
directions: Coat 10-inch pie pan with cooking spray. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl. Make a well in center. In large measuring cup, whisk butter, egg, milk and vanilla. Pour into well. Stir until evenly moistened. Pour into pie pan. Toss blueberries, sugar and cinnamon in bowl. Arrange over dough. Pat with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and sage.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In a skillet over medium-high heat in hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Push chicken aside.
Stir soup and water in skillet to loosen brown bits.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: buffalo-style chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings.
Halve wings at joint.
In food processor or blender, process onion soup mix, butter, vinegar, water, garlic, pepper and cumin until blended.
Set aside.
Broil chicken 12 minutes or until brown, turning after 6 minutes.
Brush with 1/2 of soup mixture, then broil 2 minutes or until crisp. Turn, then brush with remaining soup mixture and broil an additional minute.
Serve with Wish-Bone Chunky Blue Cheese dressing and celery sticks.

title: individual pizzas(method:  box oven)
directions: Shred salami with knife or shears.
Roll biscuit dough very thin.
Cut into 12 rounds (5 1/2 inches in diameter).
Place on cookie sheet and flute edges.
Spread with tomato paste; sprinkle with oregano (1/8 to 1 1/4 teaspoons per round).
Top with salami and cheese.
Bake until biscuits are brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook and stir until boils and is thick.

title: noodles
directions: Boil water and cook spaghetti noodles.
Sit in fridge (open, no lid) for 3 hours.
Put in bowl.
Warm in microwave 15 seconds.
Add 5 drops of water and shake of salt.
Warm for 20 more seconds in microwave.
Add butter and 2 shakes of salt.
Stir; warm for 30 seconds.
Eat.

title: chess squares
directions: Stir together the cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Pat into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and confectioners sugar and spread on other mixture. Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Fill cupcake paper 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until dry.
Put one spoonful cherry pie filling on each or any pie filling of your choice. Makes 2 dozen.

title: copper pennies
directions: Bring to a boil, then simmer 15 minutes. Alternate layers of cooked sliced carrots, onions and green peppers in dish.
Pour hot sauce over. Refrigerate. Gets better the longer left.

title: ravioli pie
directions: Cook ravioli in boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Spray one 9-inch round cake pan with cooking spray. Coat bottom of pan with sauce.
Place a layer of ravioli over sauce.
Continue layering until pan is full. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and place a layer of Mozzarella on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly.

title: taco bowls #1
directions: Heat 3 inches Crisco oil in deep fryer or heavy saucepan to 375°.
Place 1 tortilla in oil.
Let float 5 to 10 seconds.
Press center of tortilla into oil with metal ladle (tortilla will form a bowl shape).
While pressing with metal ladle, fry 1 to 2 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Fill as desired.

title: pumpkin and raisin cake
directions: Beat sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs in mixer bowl.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl; mix well.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute. Stir in pineapple, raisins, 1 cup pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool completely.
Spread Nutty Cream Cheese Frosting over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup pecans.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: farmer's garlic bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add ingredients, stirring over heat until blended.
Remove from heat and brush on Italian or French bread slices.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and milk and place in bottom of a
greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Mix together butter, blackberries, 3/4 cup sugar and 3/4 cup water and pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Other fruit may be substituted for blackberries.

title: out of this world fudge balls
directions: On stove or in microwave, melt chocolate and butter.
Add egg and beat until smooth and glossy.
Add 10x sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Chill about 1 hour.
When firm, shape into 1 1/4-inch balls. Roll in coconut.
Keep balls refrigerated until ready to use. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush 3/4 of the package of Oreos to cover the bottom of a pan. Second, make your pudding and pour all of it on top of the Oreos, then spread smoothly the Cool Whip on top of the pudding.
Fourth step is to crush and sprinkle remaining 1/4 of the Oreos on top of the Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Marinate shrimp in lemon juice and oil in Pyrex dish for 2 hours.
Cook and drain rice.
Saute onion and pepper in butter for 2 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: wild pheasant (or chicken) and rice
directions: Place the uncooked rice in bottom of casserole.
Arrange chicken on rice.
Sprinkle generously with garlic salt.
Mix the soup, cream (no milk), parsley and paprika.
Pour over pheasant and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until done. Take chicken off bones and put back into broth, if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain and put in casserole dish.
Cook garden peas on High for 5 minutes.
After peas come to a boil, drain and pour on top of hamburger meat.
Fix instant potatoes according to directions on box.
Put on top of garden peas. Spread evenly, then sprinkle cheese over top of potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: old fashioned syrup cookies
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, shortening and egg until well blended.
Add soda, vinegar and spice.
Mix quickly.
Add flour gradually.
Roll out thin and cut with cookie cutter, if desired.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until browned around edges.
Do not burn.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Mix soups and onion together.
Pour over beef stew meat.
Bake in 275° oven for 4 hours, covered.

title: angel squares
directions: Mix according to directions.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use 17-inch jelly roll pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add lemon juice and water to make 2 cups. Add sugar and bring to boil.
Add dissolved gelatin and cool.
Add green peppers, celery, mayonnaise and onion to taste.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bran apple cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and soda.
Add cheese, cereal and apple; mix lightly.
Add margarine and egg, mixing just until moistened.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend chocolate and water; add 5 dry ingredients.
Mix in the rest.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: kolachy
directions: Combine oleo and cream cheese; beat until smooth and creamy. Add vanilla.
Mix in flour and salt, mixing to a soft dough. Divide in half; wrap in plastic wrap and chill until firm.
Roll out dough to 1/8 inch and cut into squares about 2 inches.
Spoon 1/2 tsp. of fruit spread onto each square; fold 2 corners to middle.
*Note:
All fruit spreads are good, or poppy seed filling can be used, also apricot.
Beat egg with water; brush edges before folding; pinch to seal.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown in a 375° oven.

title: favorite family dip
directions: Mix with mixer until smooth. Serve. Refrigerate for storage.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in a dishpan in the order given. Drop by balls on baking sheet.
Do not overbake.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.

title: bacon-baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and stir well.
Spread in baking dish and bake until top is browned, about 10 minutes.

title: pineapple-lime nectar
directions: Combine fruit juices and sugar.
Divide among 6 tall ice-filled glasses.
Fill with ginger ale.
If desired, garnish with fresh cherries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh orange salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and blend well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill.
Can be served on lettuce leaves with Ritz or saltine crackers with green cherry on top.

title: mom-mom's creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Grease a 4-quart pan with margarine on the bottom and sides. Add margarine, sugar and evaporated milk; stir and heat (using candy thermometer) until soft ball stage, about 15 to 20 minutes over medium-high heat.
When mixture reaches soft ball stage, remove from heat.
Add chocolate bits, Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla; stir briskly until smooth.
Add nuts, if desired, and immediately pour into two greased 9 x 11-inch pans.
Let stand until cool.
Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cut eggs into pieces.
Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator, if desired, for better flavor.

title: pound cake with rum nut topping
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla. Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts in well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: cool pie
directions: Beat together milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: caesar salad
directions: In a wooden bowl, mash garlic and salt. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Mix well. Break raw egg; beat well and add oil. Tear lettuce into bite-size. Mix croutons with lettuce and pour dressing over the mixture. Add Parmesan cheese and stir. I began using the egg substitutes and they work just as well as the raw egg. Makes enough dressing for 4 or 5 salads.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Just before serving, combine and add:

title: no bake fruit drops
directions: In bowl, mix cereal, sugar and fruit until well combined.
Stir in corn syrup.
Knead cereal mixture with lightly greased hands until mixture holds together.
Shape into 20 (1 inch) balls, roll in chopped almonds.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 20 cookies, 60 calories; 6 mg. sodium; 1 gram fat each.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Cream well.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Stir until moist.
Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until middle springs back when pressed.

title: olivia's applesauce cake(cake made in "the homecoming" from the walton's t.v. show)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: country fried pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops, mushrooms and onion.
(Use a tablespoon of shortening if necessary.)
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and thyme.
Add carrots.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Serve over noodles. Optional:
Cut up pork pieces instead of pork chops.

title: 24 hour dessert
directions: Crush vanilla wafers real fine. Spread in bottom of glass dish. Mix powdered sugar and Crisco together and spread over vanilla wafer crumbs. Put pineapple over sugar mixture. Whip whipping cream and spread over pineapple. Cover. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients for 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Reduce heat and add soup and cheese.
Simmer until well mixed and cheese is melted, stirring often to keep from sticking.

title: breakaway bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over shortening and dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, flour and add dissolved yeast.
Mix well in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit into melted butter and stack in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Break apart.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Heat corn; put through sieve.
Combine celery, chicken and broth in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir hot milk into egg yolks gradually.
Add to soup mixture and corn.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Serve with croutons.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in oleo until crumbly. Sprinkle over top of apples.
Cook, uncovered, 12 minutes in microwave.
If you prefer a more crunchy brown topping place under the broiler for a few minutes.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix soups with 1 can milk.
Butter large baking dish or deep roasting pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom.
Heat soups with milk and mix well.
Pour soup mixture over rice.
Lay pieces of chicken (uncooked) over rice and soup.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over each piece of chicken; pepper if desired.
Paprika may be sprinkled on top.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 2 hours.
Remove cover last 1/2 or 3/4 hour to brown if desired.

title: oriental microwave chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts, meat side up, barely overlapping.
Cook on 80% power for 10 minutes.
Rotate after 5 minutes if no turntable.
Turn over each breast.
Cook 10 minutes at 80% power. Rotate after 5. Turn over one more time.
Cook 5 minutes to finish. Pierce to check complete doneness.
Cook 5 minutes more, if necessary.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix lightly.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly, then remove from pan.
Can freeze.

title: cookie candy
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
In a large bowl (glass), combine sugar and Karo syrup.
Cook on High in microwave until mixture boils.
Remove from microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Remove shells from eggs; cut into small pieces. Combine peas, eggs and soup. Mix well. Cover with grated cheese. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top, then pour melted margarine over all. Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and top is golden brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into 1 (9-inch) pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and after chicken is done, boil the spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute the peppers, onions and celery.
Add cream of chicken soup, Cheddar cheese soup, cheese and garlic salt.
Mix all ingredients together and heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strudel
directions: Mix together oleo, milk, egg yolks and flour. Brush top with oleo, cover tight.
Chill overnight or longer in refrigerator. When
ready
to
roll
out,
sprinkle cloth well with flour
and roll dough with rolling pin.
Divide into 5 parts. Roll
out
very thin.
Grease dough with oleo.
Add apples or pears,
sugar, cinnamon,
fruit,
vanilla
wafers
(crushed), pecans, coconut and raisins.
Sprinkle a lot of oleo on top of that
and
roll
up like jelly roll.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° or 325° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sugar-free spiced pumpkin pie
directions: Beat pumpkin, milk and eggs in medium bowl.
Beat in remaining ingredients and pour into a low-fat pie crust.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
