Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: vineyard cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Put in plastic bag and shape. Chill.
Serve with crackers.
This can be made ahead and frozen. Yield:
1 cheese ball.

title: special peanut butter fudge
directions: Use a wooden spoon (this is part of the secret).
Grease sides and bottom of large cookie sheet.
Grease sides and bottom of large saucepan.
Mix margarine, evaporated milk, white sugar and salt.
Mix well and place over medium heat, bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook about 6minutes, test a few drops in cold water.
When a soft ball forms, remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Again, mix well and as soon as all ingredients dissolve, pour into sheet.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours before marking. Yields 4 1/2 pounds.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside. In microwave-safe bowl, heat chips and oil on Medium-high for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Microwave on High for 10 seconds; stir until smooth. Pour over the cereals and mix well.
Spread on a waxed paper-lined baking sheet. Cool and break apart.
Store in airtight container. Yields 5 quarts.

title: four ingredient soup
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Combine the four ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onions in oleo, combine with soups and green peppers. Add chicken; beat well; place layer of chicken, layer of tortillas, layer of sauce, layer of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes six servings.

title: best ever bean soup
directions: The secret to a really good soup is not to skimp on the meat!

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add enough warm broth or water to make stiff dough of flour and egg mixture.
Work out very thin.
Cut into narrow strips. Let stand 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Cook chicken until tender. Remove skin and bones.
Put chicken in broth.
Add soup; bring to a boil.
Add dumpling strips a few at a time.
Boil after each addition.
Simmer until dumplings are done.
If too dry, add water or chicken soup to broth.

title: mam-maw's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together in an ice cream freezer container.
Finish to the ring with milk.
Pack container in the ice cream freezer with ice and salt.
Start churning.
(Be sure to follow instructions on the salt box for best results.)

title: tomato pudding
directions: In a medium size casserole dish, oiled with olive oil, place a layer of sliced bread.
Drizzle it with olive oil.
Place tomato slices on the bread (slices should be fairly thick). Sprinkle with cheeses, herbs, salt and pepper.
Continue layering bread and tomatoes until casserole is full, with the last layer being bread. Drizzle oil on top layer. Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole is hot.

title: no-milk parker house rolls
directions: Add oil, salt, sugar and yeast to water.
Stir in flour; cover and set in warm place to rise.
When doubled in bulk, add egg. Knead lightly and let rise again.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Crease in center with dull knife.
Brush with melted butter and fold over, pinching at sides.

title: holiday sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Place balls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans in a crock-pot
directions: Presoak beans in cold water for 4 to 5 hours.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
May need to add more water as it cooks.

title: gram alice's toffee topping
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover warm cake and broil 5 minutes.

title: surprise meringue kisses
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beat until very stiff peaks form.
Drop by tablespoon 1 1/2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press a kiss into each cookie, not all the way through. With a table knife, bring meringue up over candy.
Bake in 275° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove to rack and cool.
Store in tight container.

title: mock chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into buttered casserole and bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: brazilian pickled onions
directions: In a heat-proof bowl, cover onion rings with boiling water for 15 seconds; drain immediately and cool with cold water.
Drain again.
Mix the other three ingredients and beat with a fork. Pour over onion rings and toss.
Let sit at least 1/2 hour at room temperature.
Do not refrigerate.

title: yogurt bread
directions: Dissolve warm water and dry yeast.
Add yogurt, honey and salt.
Mix in flour to semi-soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Divide into 2 loaves.
Put into 2 pans.
Oil top.
Cover with Saran Wrap and raise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt bea's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoon on baking sheet.
Bake until brown at 325°.

title: green rice salad
directions: In a large saucepan, bring rice, water and 1 teaspoon salt to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let set 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: jerked venison
directions: Mix melted oleo, vinegar and bacon grease.
Add spices and brown sugar. Dip cut up meat in warm sauce.
Leave in pickle 3 days, turning once a day.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a 9
x 13-inch
greased and floured pan.	Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes;
bake
for
minutes if using a glass pan. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: charlotte's coleslaw
directions: Combine dressing ingredients.
Mix well. Toss with shredded cabbage. Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fried venison
directions: Soak venison slices in buttermilk for at least 10 minutes. Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Dip venison in flour or place flour in plastic bag.
Add venison and shake to coat.
Fry in oil until well done.
Drain.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine soup and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: red potatoes with parmesan cheese
directions: Place melted butter in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over butter and add chopped garlic.
Place potatoes, cut side down, in butter mix.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: liver spread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: old-fashioned lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a heavy saucepan. Gradually add milk, stirring until blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot mixture; stirring constantly, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken on wax paper covered with flour; cover chicken with flour and another piece of wax paper.
Beat with mallet until as flat as possible.
Turn over; more flour and beat.
Layer a piece of ham and Swiss cheese on top of chicken; roll.
Dip in egg with milk and seasoning, then in flour, then in bread crumbs.
Dip twice if desired.
Place in dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add the powdered sugar and blend real good.
Stir in the fruit cocktail and pecans.
Pour into the graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Spread half the Cool Whip in bottom of deep dish.
Spread Oreo cookie crumbs over this and spoon pineapple over cookies.
Now, add the other half of Cool Whip over this.
Garnish with grated cookies and cherries.
Chill.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs and buttermilk. Add flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix in oil and cereal. Allow batter to set for 24 hours.
Keep covered in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Can bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave approximately 2 to 3 minutes.

title: old southwest cheese soup
directions: In a large stock-pot, add green chili sauce, tomatoes, diced chili and chicken broth. Heat over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking, for 15 minutes or until warm throughout.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar, instant minced onion and oregano. Add butter, wine, cheese, egg and milk. Beat until well blended. Turn into well greased 8-inch round baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl. Add beer all at once. Break eggs into bowl before mixing. Blend until mixed well. Dough will have thick consistency.
Put in greased bread pans. Bake for 40 minutes at 375°. Loaves will be like English muffins when done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a 4-cup Pyrex container.
Add sugar, cocoa and salt; blend well.
Gradually add milk, stirring well. Micro-cook on Full power for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, until thickened. Stir 2 or 3 times.
Watch closely at the end of cooking to prevent boiling over.
Store in glass jar and refrigerate.
To use, remove lid and heat 3/4 to 1 minute.
Stir and pour over ice cream.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over brisket. Sprinkle with celery, onion and garlic salts. Refrigerate overnight in covered pan. Sprinkle both sides with table salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 200° to 225° for 4 to 5 hours or until tender. Uncover and pour barbecue sauce over meat. Bake 1 hour longer. Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: southwest dip(also known as mexi dip)
directions: Mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Blend well. Set aside.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and ground nuts like pie dough.
Pat evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spoon over crust.

title: dip and bits
directions: Mix everything in one bowl; refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water to prevent sticking.
Add tuna and peas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spray casserole dish with Pam or other vegetable oil spray.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Can add grated cheese, if desired, prior to baking.

title: swiss cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line one 9 inch pie plate with pastry. Spread crust evenly with softened butter; chill well.
With wire whisk, beat eggs. cream and salt.
Stir in cheese.
Pour egg mixture into crust.
Bake 15 minutes; turn oven to 325°.
Bake 35 minutes.
Quiche is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook the sausage over medium heat until no longer pink, drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.

title: spaghetti al fresco
directions: Combine eggs, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cut pork in 1/4-inch pieces.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In large frypan, cook pork in olive oil over medium heat until well browned.
Add mushrooms and butter; cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water; drain.
Add to pork mixture; blend well.
Transfer to deep platter.
Pour egg mixture over spaghetti.
Lift and turn with serving fork and spoon.
Sprinkle with cheese; lift and turn until well mixed. Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Mix milk, shortening and egg; add to flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Fold in strawberries, nuts and raisins.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling, extract and eggs.
By hand, stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate pieces until smooth.
Pour over still warm bars.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion until onion is soft.
Add broccoli and cook until defrosted.
Take off stove.
Add Cheez Whiz, Minute rice and cream of celery soup.
Mix well and place in an ungreased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (uncovered).

title: mary ellen's tea cakes
directions: Bake at 350° until it sinks in (approximately 5 to 8 minutes).

title: blue cheese dressing(low calorie)
directions: Place cottage cheese, milk and lemon juice in blender.
Blend at medium speed.
Fold in Blue cheese.
Keep in jar in refrigerator until used.
Makes approximately 1 cup.
There are 21 calories per tablespoon.

title: smothered corn and chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces generously with salt, cayenne and black pepper.
In a heavy, iron pot, put enough oil to cover the bottom of the pot.
Over moderately high heat, brown the chicken pieces. Remove and set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add eggs, buttermilk and cooking oil.
Bake in muffin tins 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked acorn squash with stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut squash in half.
Remove seeds. Place cut side down on baking sheet sprayed with vegetable pan spray.
Combine apples, celery and onion.
Add margarine and water.
Put in small baking dish.
Cover.
Bake squash and apple stuffing
for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove from oven.
Salt squash.
Fill with apple mixture.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix together meal, sugar, salt and 1/2 stick margarine.
Scald with 3 cups of boiling water. Add beaten eggs and hot milk.
Pour into heavy 10-inch skillet in which 1/2 stick margarine has been melted.
Bake at 400° until brown, then reduce heat to 350°.
Time about 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook green peppers and onion with garlic until tender; stir to separate meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: golden cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter in dish in oven.
Quarter and peel potatoes. Combine 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and 1/4 cup flour in plastic bags. Shake potatoes in mixture.
Season and bake in butter at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Makes 3 meat loaves with 2 pounds of ground beef or chuck.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and oatmeal and set aside for two hours.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Mix flour, spices and soda.
Combine oatmeal, egg and flour mixtures.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add egg and salt;
stir good. Add sour milk, soda, vanilla and flour.
Add cut up rhubarb; pour batter in oblong pan and sprinkle mixture of 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy but fancy cookies
directions: Cream butter; add vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Shape into 2 rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill 1 hour.

title: 10 minute chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan or microwave, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: blueberry cake with lemon glaze
directions: Combine 3 cups cake flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour mixture over blueberries and toss gently to coat; set aside.

title: perky potatoes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with foil. Let stand until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: easy spicy apple mold
directions: Heat water in a medium saucepan.
Dissolve the cinnamon candies in the hot water.
Add apples. Cook until apples are tender.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Pour into your prettiest mold.
Excellent served with ham.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until fork-tender; drain.
Add cheese and oleo while hot.
Mix other ingredients into broccoli.
Place into casserole dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, in oven for 40 minutes (350°).

title: mom's soft sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine butter, sugar, egg and flavoring in mixing bowl and cream.
Add sour cream and half of flour mixture and blend.
Add remaining flour and stir in by hand. Set oven at 400° to preheat.
Divide dough in half and roll each part on lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with sugar, roll in lightly.
Cut with floured cutter.
Lift to greased cookie sheet with pancake turner.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and decorate.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together until fluffy.

title: chicken dumplings dish
directions: Melt margarine in large glass baking dish.
Dredge seasoned chicken on both sides in the butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes uncovered.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour mixture over chicken pieces.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Drop dumplings into gravy.
Bake uncovered until dumplings are light brown.

title: smoked picnic and oven pea soup
directions: In a deep roaster, with cover, combine all ingredients except picnic ham.
Do not add salt.
Top with picnic ham, cover and place in cold oven.
Then bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours or until peas are very tender and mushy.
Lift meat from soup.
Slice and serve hot or cool.
Refrigerate for future use.

title: strawberry peach ice cream
directions: Combine strawberries and peaches.
Stir in condensed milk, evaporated milk, half & half and milk.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla extract.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into ice cream canister and pour in additional milk to the proper level for your make of ice cream freezer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift flour with salt and soda; add to above.
Add vanilla, nuts, oats and chocolate bits; mix well.
Drop scant teaspoons.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Make a dough by combining oleo, sugar, eggs, vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Spread 1/2 of the dough on a cookie sheet. Carefully spoon pie filling over dough.
Then spread other half of dough over filling and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Add Jell-O, boiling water and ice cream; stir until melted. Chill until thick.
Fold in 1 pint of drained strawberries.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Enough for 2 pies.

title: crazy beans
directions: Chop Sizzlean into small pieces; fry until brown. Remove meat from pan and discard all but small amount of fat. Dice onions and saute in the fat. Add brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cool dessert
directions: Mix cottage cheese and pineapple.
Sprinkle jello over and mix well.
Then stir in Cool Whip.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and water in heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until clear. Cook without stirring to 240°.
Beat egg whites at room temperature to soft peaks; continue to beat slowly, adding syrup mixture.
Add flavorings.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form and frosting is thick enough.

title: antipasto bread
directions: Pat out 1 roll of crescent rolls in lightly greased 9 x 13 pan. Alternately with the salami, Provolone, ham, Swiss, pepperoni and Mozzarella. Cover with drained roasted peppers. Scramble the 2 eggs. Add salt and pepper and crushed garlic. Pour over peppers. Take other roll of
crescent rolls and cover. Scramble egg yolk and brush. Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1/2 hour and covered for 1/2 hour more.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake,	then
mash
sweet
potatoes.	 Add
remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour
into remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth, gradually beating in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla flavoring. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust and chill until set, at least 2 hours. Top with strawberries, if desired.

title: red kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water, pineapple juice and lemon juice together.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: The pie that does the impossible by making its own crust.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4 or 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add juice alternately with flour.
Add nuts and raisins last.
Bake in a tube pan.
Place pan of water over top of cake for 2 hours, baking at 250°.
Then take water out and raise heat to 300° and bake about 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: chateau lake trout
directions: Place one headless trout on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Insert several slices of butter and seasoning inside the trout.
Wrap trout in foil so it's sealed.
Cook trout over hot coals or an open flame.
Cook for approximately 5 to 7 minutes on each side. Cooking time will vary depending on temperature.
Remove from heat. Open foil and allow several minutes to cool.
Hold trout and flake off one side fillet from bone.
Turn trout over and repeat.
All bones should be removed by using this method.
Serve.

title: green peppers with cheese rice
directions: Wash green peppers.
Cut off tops and remove seeds.
Steam peppers, tops included, until barely tender.
Cook rice by package directions (leftover rice can be used).
Saute onion and mushrooms until soft in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place drained peppers in an oiled baking dish.
Spoon in rice mixture. Replace tops.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: "so good" sweet potato holiday bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: henry warthman's dump cake
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a pan.
Dot butter on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pistol lettes
directions: Crumble sausage and hamburger.
Fry until done.
Drain all the grease from mixture.
Make sure hamburger and sausage is mixed well.
Cut cheese in small pieces and blend into the meat mixture until the cheese is completely melted and blended in.
Place on hamburger bun.
Heat in oven until bread is brown.
Serve.

title: eggplant oriental
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake the eggplant for 30 minutes until soft.
In the oil, saute onion, garlic, parsley, bell peppers and tomatoes.
Add spices.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add tomato paste, ketchup, chili sauce and eggplant.
Cook for 20 more minutes.
Puree in a blender; serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: mrs. waffsie's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in eggs and sour cream. Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder and add to cream mixture.
Set aside.
Mix chopped nuts and sugar in another bowl.
Pour half of batter in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle half of nut-sugar topping.
Add top layer of batter.
Sprinkle on remaining topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.
A New Year's morning tradition in the Worth family.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard, cayenne pepper and garlic powder until smooth. Fold in artichoke hearts and crab. Can be served hot or cold with crackers or bread.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers. Mix pudding mix with milk until set. Fold in Cool Whip. Put half over graham crackers. Repeat process. Microwave tub of frosting until soft. Pour over cake to cover completely.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
While mixing at low speed, add sour cream alternately with the dry ingredients, into the cream mixture, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, raisins, and walnuts in a large bowl.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk and soy sauce.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 fried onions.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 minutes, stirring halfway.
Sprinkle with remaining onions; microwave, uncovered, for 1 minute.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Heat until butter melts.
Place chicken in shallow glass dish and brush with sauce.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cooking.
Grill chicken.

title: honey dijon dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.

title: bonbons
directions: Melt in top half of double boiler.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: With fork, crumb and mix together first 6 ingredients.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture and combine with Heath bars.
Heat buttermilk and egg together for 3 minutes.
Add to the first mixture.
Spread in large 9 x 13-inch greased pan; top with Heath bar mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled pork chops with pineapple
directions: In a dish, combine dressing, juice, sugar and soy.
Add chops and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, for 3 hours or overnight.
Remove chops and bring marinade to a boil.
Grill or broil chops, basting with marinade until done.
Meanwhile, grill or broil pineapple brushed with marinade until golden.
Bring remaining marinade to a boil and serve over chops.

title: apple cake cobbler
directions: In 9 x 13 inch pan, spread pie filling evenly over bottom, sprinkle cinnamon over top. Evenly, spread dry cake mix
next. Mix brown sugar and nuts together and spread over top. Lay the butter patties over all, covering entire top of cake.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef lightly in butter or margarine in a medium sized frying pan, break up with a fork as it cooks.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Stir constantly until sauce is bubbly hot.
Stir in sour cream just before ready to serve; heat just to boiling; remove from heat as gravy may curdle.
Serve over hot noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: marinated beef
directions: Combine vinegar, ketchup, oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder; blend well.
Pour marinade over meat and refrigerate several hours or overnight; turn often.
Allow meat to stand in marinade for 30 minutes at room temperature.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Cut into thin, diagonal slices.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mama's blackberry cake(over 50 years old)
directions: *If you want to use self-rising flour, omit salt and baking powder.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle on cheese, then sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper. Pour egg mixture over the bread, sausage and cheese.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apricot whip salad
directions: Heat pineapple in juice.
Sprinkle Jell-O over top of pineapple and mix well.
Let set until cool.
Add buttermilk and fold in Cool Whip. Chill until firm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender in small amount of water; remove from bone and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Saute green pepper, garlic and onions in little salad oil.
Add chicken broth and then add tomatoes, chili and mushroom liquid.
Simmer mixture slowly until chili is dissolved, about 30 minutes.
Cook vermicelli as directed on box.
In large (or two medium) casserole, put layers of vermicelli, cheese, chicken and chili mixture.
On top layer place mushrooms and more cheese.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 16 to 20 servings

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat mixture until boiling, then add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: billie's millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate. Best when served cold.

title: wedding mints (cream cheese)
directions: Combine and make into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press into rubber molds from cake shop, Ben Franklin's or anywhere that carries Wilton supplies.
Yields 140 mints to 2 boxes of sugar.

title: pickled cranberries
directions: In a 2-quart non-aluminum saucepan, combine water, vinegar, sugar and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add cranberries.
Return to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool, then chill cranberries in syrup.

title: superb baked scallops
directions: Thaw scallops if frozen.
Rinse scallops with cold water to remove any remaining shell particles.
Cut large scallops in half. Combine scallops, cracker crumbs, margarine, catsup, salt, sugar and pepper.
Place equal amounts of scallop mixture in 6 well-greased 10 ounce casseroles or place scallop mixture into a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket.
Let cool.
Layer in chunks in bottom of casserole dish.
Dice onions on top of potatoes.
Dice eggs on top of that.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, and mustard together, then pour over potatoes.
Mix.
Crumble bacon on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Bake pastry shells.
In pan, cook pepper in oleo until tender. Add soup, milk, poultry and pimento.
Heat, stirring constantly. Spoon into patty shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar one tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla and beat until peaks stand up.
(Do not underbeat.)
Cover pie well and brown in a 350° oven, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given, folding in the beaten egg white last.
Place mixture in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese. Blend in egg yolk and vanilla. Add cake mix 1/3 at a time; mix well. If mixer is used, add last part of cake mix by hand. Chill dough 1/2 hour. Heat oven to 375° (quick moderate). Drop by scant teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until delicately browned. Cool cookies before removing from baking sheet. Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: crabapple jelly
directions: Day One:
Wash and quarter apples.
Place in large kettle. Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Let simmer until tender.

title: swiss-spinach quiche
directions: Place biscuits in ungreased 9-inch quiche pan (or 9-inch pie pan), pressing pieces together to form a crust.
Toss cheese with flour.
Combine milk, eggs and seasoning.
Add cheese mixture and spinach; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until it forms a hard ball in cold water, then add oats and peanut butter.
Drop with a teaspoon on wax paper.
Let get hard.

title: butterfingers
directions: Mix well.
Shape into small fingers.
Place on waxed paper and put in freezer.
Chill until firm.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Cream Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses, mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Do not flatten cookies.
Makes 24 soft cookies.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour uncooked macaroni into melted butter, and stir until macaroni is covered well.
Stir salt, pepper and cheese through macaroni.
Pour milk over all, and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: twenty minute pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 20 minutes.
Put in a lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Do not preheat oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape meatballs into small balls. Fry in 1/2 inch oil.
Shake while cooking to prevent burning.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine salt and cucumbers; let stand 5 hours or overnight.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in 375° oven or will be done when knife blade comes clean when tested in center.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until mixture boils.
Turn heat low and continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits, Karo, margarine and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate has melted and fudge is smooth.
Add nuts and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered pan.
Spread and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: fruit and brownie pizza
directions: Spray a 12-inch pizza pan with nonstick coating; set the pan aside.
For crust, combine margarine and sugar in a medium size mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add egg product and beat well.
Alternately add the 3/4 cup chocolate flavored syrup and flour, beating after each addition at low speed until combined.
Spread mixture in the prepared pizza pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
To serve, cut crust into 12 wedges.
Top each wedge with some of the fruit. Drizzle each with remaining chocolate flavored syrup.
Makes 12 servings.
Per Serving:
calories, 159; total fat, 3 grams; saturated fat, 1 gram; cholesterol, 0 mg; sodium, 54 grams; carbohydrates, 33 grams; fiber, 1 gram and protein, 2 grams.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Blend oil and flour and seasonings in heavy pan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir well to help the melting.
Serve over eggs or cooked vegetables of your choice.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend flour and butter or margarine as you would for pie crust.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch greased cake pan.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350°, until set and golden.
Cool.

title: orange delight
directions: Heat marshmallows; add ginger ale, juice and Dream Whip.
Fold into broken cake pieces.
Chill.

title: dilly tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy.

title: black forest mousse
directions: In large bowl, beat chocolate with condensed milk.
Beat in water, then pudding mix and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Freeze 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into dishes.
Stir remaining 1/4 teaspoon extract into cherry filling; spoon over dessert.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese; dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine the remaining ingredients and top ingredients in pan.

title: magic (7 layer) bars
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Layer remaining ingredients, pouring milk over last.
Microwave on Roast/Medium for 12 to 15 minutes (in glass pan).
Or, bake in regular oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: pea casserole
directions: Saute in 1/2 stick butter the first 3 ingredients; add to peas.
Then add pimento, water chestnuts and soup.
Spread buttered bread crumbs over top.

title: mexican appetizer dish
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 8 x 8-inch microwave-proof dish.
Spread chili on top.
(You probably will use only about 3/4 of the can.)
Sprinkle cheese on top to cover.
Microwave for about 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill and serve on a bed of lettuce, garnished with sliced, hard-cooked eggs.

title: blender macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Toss with margarine and place in casserole dish.
Place all other ingredients in blender and blend until thick and mushy.
Pour over macaroni.
Cover with 1/2 cup crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Can also use steak.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix cooled and chopped chicken breasts with other ingredients and chill.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 45 minutes or until well done.

title: the black dog black-out frosting
directions: Sift sugar with cocoa in a small bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan over medium heat, mix cream with honey, butter and vanilla.
Stir in the cocoa/sugar mixture.
Using a whisk, stir for 8 to 10 minutes, until mixture is completely smooth.
Do not boil! Remove from heat and cover surface of mixture with plastic wrap. Cool in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours, until thick enough to use. Whip with a mixer until light and fluffy.
Chocolate lovers should use this on a chocolate cake!

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add eggs, milk, butter or margarine, cheese and onion.
Drain the thawed spinach well.
Add to mixture. Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until bubbly and lightly golden. Let stand about 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over hot water.
Mix confectioners sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Stick with a toothpick and dip in chocolate/paraffin mixture.
Do not cover completely.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten well until lemon colored. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and flavorings.
Spoon mixture into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
